var book = {
	"name": "Deuteronomy",
	"numChapters": 34,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>These are the words which Moses spoke to all Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4894A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4894A\"></sup>across the Jordan in the wilderness, in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4894B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4894B\"></sup>Arabah opposite Suph, between Paran and Tophel and Laban and Hazeroth and Dizahab.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It is eleven days’ <i>journey</i> from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4895C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4895C\"></sup>Horeb by the way of Mount <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4895D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4895D\"></sup>Seir to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4895E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4895E\"></sup>Kadesh-barnea.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>In the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4896F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4896F\"></sup>fortieth year, on the first <i>day</i> of the eleventh month, Moses spoke to the children of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4896G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4896G\"></sup>according to all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded him <i>to give</i> to them,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>after he had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4897H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4897H\"></sup>defeated Sihon the king of the Amorites, who lived in Heshbon, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4897I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4897I\"></sup>Og the king of Bashan, who lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4897J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4897J\"></sup>Ashtaroth and Edrei.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Across the Jordan in the land of Moab, Moses undertook to expound this law, saying,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4899K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4899K\"></sup>spoke to us at Horeb, saying, ‘You have stayed long enough at this mountain.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Turn and set your journey, and go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4900L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4900L\"></sup>the hill country of the Amorites, and to all their neighbors in the Arabah, in the hill country and in the lowland and in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4900M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4900M\"></sup>the Negev and by the seacoast, the land of the Canaanites, and Lebanon, as far as the great river, the river Euphrates.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>See, I have placed the land before you; go in and possess the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4901N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4901N\"></sup>swore to give to your fathers, to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, to them and their descendants after them.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“I spoke to you at that time, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4902O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4902O\"></sup>I am not able to bear <i>the burden</i> of you alone.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4903P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4903P\"></sup>multiplied you, and behold, you are this day like the stars of heaven in number.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, increase you a thousand-fold more than you are and bless you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4904Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4904Q\"></sup>just as He has promised you!",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>How can I alone bear the load and burden of you and your strife?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4906R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4906R\"></sup>Choose wise and discerning and experienced men from your tribes, and I will appoint them as your heads.’",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You answered me and said, ‘The thing which you have said to do is good.’",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So I took the heads of your tribes, wise and experienced men, and appointed them heads over you, leaders of thousands and of hundreds, of fifties and of tens, and officers for your tribes.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Then I charged your judges at that time, saying, ‘Hear <i>the cases</i> between your fellow countrymen, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4909S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4909S\"></sup>judge righteously between a man and his fellow countryman, or the alien who is with him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4910T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4910T\"></sup>You shall not show partiality in judgment; you shall hear the small and the great alike. You shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4910U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4910U\"></sup>not fear man, for the judgment is God’s. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4910V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4910V\"></sup>The case that is too hard for you, you shall bring to me, and I will hear it.’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4911W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4911W\"></sup>I commanded you at that time all the things that you should do.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Then we set out from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4912X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4912X\"></sup>Horeb, and went through all that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4912Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4912Y\"></sup>great and terrible wilderness which you saw on the way to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4912Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4912Z\"></sup>hill country of the Amorites, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God had commanded us; and we came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4912AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4912AA\"></sup>Kadesh-barnea.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>I said to you, ‘You have come to the hill country of the Amorites which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God is about to give us.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>See, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has placed the land before you; go up, take possession, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, has spoken to you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4914AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4914AB\"></sup>Do not fear or be dismayed.’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4915AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4915AC\"></sup>Then all of you approached me and said, ‘Let us send men before us, that they may search out the land for us, and bring back to us word of the way by which we should go up and the cities which we shall enter.’",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The thing pleased me and I took twelve of your men, one man for each tribe.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4917AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4917AD\"></sup>They turned and went up into the hill country, and came to the valley of Eshcol and spied it out.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then they took <i>some</i> of the fruit of the land in their hands and brought it down to us; and they brought us back a report and said, ‘It is a good land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God is about to give us.’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4919AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4919AE\"></sup>Yet you were not willing to go up, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4919AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4919AF\"></sup>rebelled against the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God;",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4920AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4920AG\"></sup>you grumbled in your tents and said, ‘Because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> hates us, He has brought us out of the land of Egypt to deliver us into the hand of the Amorites to destroy us.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Where can we go up? Our brethren have made our hearts melt, saying, “The people are bigger and taller than we; the cities are large and fortified to heaven. And besides, we saw <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4921AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4921AH\"></sup>the sons of the Anakim there.”’",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then I said to you, ‘Do not be shocked, nor fear them.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God who goes before you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4923AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4923AI\"></sup>Himself fight on your behalf, just as He did for you in Egypt before your eyes,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and in the wilderness where you saw how <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4924AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4924AJ\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God carried you, just as a man carries his son, in all the way which you have walked until you came to this place.’",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4925AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4925AK\"></sup>for all this, you did not trust the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4926AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4926AL\"></sup>who goes before you on <i>your</i> way, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4926AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4926AM\"></sup>to seek out a place for you to encamp, in fire by night and cloud by day, to show you the way in which you should go.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heard the sound of your words, and He was angry and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4927AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4927AN\"></sup>took an oath, saying,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4928AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4928AO\"></sup>Not one of these men, this evil generation, shall see the good land which I swore to give your fathers,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>except Caleb the son of Jephunneh; he shall see it, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4929AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4929AP\"></sup>to him and to his sons I will give the land on which he has set foot, because he has followed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> fully.’",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4930AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4930AQ\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was angry with me also on your account, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4930AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4930AR\"></sup>Not even you shall enter there.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Joshua the son of Nun, who stands before you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4931AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4931AS\"></sup>he shall enter there; encourage him, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4931AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4931AT\"></sup>he will cause Israel to inherit it.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4932AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4932AU\"></sup>your little ones who you said would become a prey, and your sons, who this day have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4932AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4932AV\"></sup>no knowledge of good or evil, shall enter there, and I will give it to them and they shall possess it.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>But as for you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4933AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4933AW\"></sup>turn around and set out for the wilderness by the way to the Red Sea.’",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4934AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4934AX\"></sup>Then you said to me, ‘We have sinned against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; we will indeed go up and fight, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God commanded us.’ And every man of you girded on his weapons of war, and regarded it as easy to go up into the hill country.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4935AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4935AY\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘Say to them, “Do not go up nor fight, for I am not among you; otherwise you will be defeated before your enemies.”’",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>So I spoke to you, but you would not listen. Instead <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4936AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4936AZ\"></sup>you rebelled against the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and acted presumptuously and went up into the hill country.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4937BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4937BA\"></sup>The Amorites who lived in that hill country came out against you and chased you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4937BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4937BB\"></sup>as bees do, and crushed you from Seir to Hormah.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Then you returned and wept before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; but the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4938BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4938BC\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did not listen to your voice nor give ear to you.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>So you remained in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4939BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4939BD\"></sup>Kadesh many days, the days that you spent <i>there</i>."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4940A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4940A\"></sup>Then we turned and set out for the wilderness by the way to the Red Sea, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to me, and circled <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4940B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4940B\"></sup>Mount Seir for many days.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to me, saying,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>‘You have circled this mountain long enough. <i>Now</i> turn north,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4943C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4943C\"></sup>and command the people, saying, “You will pass through the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4943D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4943D\"></sup>territory of your brothers the sons of Esau who live in Seir; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4943E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4943E\"></sup>they will be afraid of you. So be very careful;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>do not provoke them, for I will not give you any of their land, even <i>as little as</i> a footstep <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4944F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4944F\"></sup>because I have given Mount Seir to Esau as a possession.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You shall buy food from them with money so that you may eat, and you shall also purchase water from them with money so that you may drink.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has blessed you in all that you have done; He has known your wanderings through this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4946G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4946G\"></sup>great wilderness. These <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4946H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4946H\"></sup>forty years the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has been with you; you have not lacked a thing.”’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“So we passed beyond our brothers the sons of Esau, who live in Seir, away from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4947I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4947I\"></sup>Arabah road, away from Elath and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4947J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4947J\"></sup>from Ezion-geber. And we turned and passed through by the way of the wilderness of Moab.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘Do not harass Moab, nor provoke them to war, for I will not give you any of their land as a possession, because I have given <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4948K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4948K\"></sup>Ar to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4948L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4948L\"></sup>the sons of Lot as a possession.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>(The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4949M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4949M\"></sup>Emim lived there formerly, a people as great, numerous, and tall as the Anakim.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Like the Anakim, they are also regarded as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4950N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4950N\"></sup>Rephaim, but the Moabites call them Emim.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4951O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4951O\"></sup>The Horites formerly lived in Seir, but the sons of Esau dispossessed them and destroyed them from before them and settled in their place, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4951P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4951P\"></sup>just as Israel did to the land of their possession which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave to them.)",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>‘Now arise and cross over the brook Zered yourselves.’ So we crossed over the brook Zered.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now the time that it took for us to come from Kadesh-barnea until we crossed over the brook Zered was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4953Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4953Q\"></sup>thirty-eight years, until <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4953R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4953R\"></sup>all the generation of the men of war perished from within the camp, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4953S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4953S\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had sworn to them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4954T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4954T\"></sup>Moreover the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was against them, to destroy them from within the camp until they all perished.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“So it came about when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4955U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4955U\"></sup>all the men of war had finally perished from among the people,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to me, saying,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>‘Today you shall cross over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4957V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4957V\"></sup>Ar, the border of Moab.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When you come opposite the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4958W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4958W\"></sup>sons of Ammon, do not harass them nor provoke them, for I will not give you any of the land of the sons of Ammon as a possession, because I have given it to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4958X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4958X\"></sup>the sons of Lot as a possession.’",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>(It is also regarded as the land of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4959Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4959Y\"></sup>Rephaim, <i>for</i> Rephaim formerly lived in it, but the Ammonites call them Zamzummin,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>a people as great, numerous, and tall as the Anakim, but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> destroyed them before them. And they dispossessed them and settled in their place,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>just as He did for the sons of Esau, who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4961Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4961Z\"></sup>live in Seir, when He destroyed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4961AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4961AA\"></sup>the Horites from before them; they dispossessed them and settled in their place even to this day.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4962AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4962AB\"></sup>Avvim, who lived in villages as far as Gaza, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4962AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4962AC\"></sup>Caphtorim who came from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4962AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4962AD\"></sup>Caphtor, destroyed them and lived in their place.)",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>‘Arise, set out, and pass through the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4963AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4963AE\"></sup>valley of Arnon. Look! I have given Sihon the Amorite, king of Heshbon, and his land into your hand; begin to take possession and contend with him in battle.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>This day I will begin to put <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4964AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4964AF\"></sup>the dread and fear of you upon the peoples everywhere under the heavens, who, when they hear the report of you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4964AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4964AG\"></sup>will tremble and be in anguish because of you.’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4965AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4965AH\"></sup>So I sent messengers from the wilderness of Kedemoth to Sihon king of Heshbon with words of peace, saying,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>‘Let me pass through your land, I will travel only on the highway; I will not turn aside to the right or to the left.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>You will sell me food for money so that I may eat, and give me water for money so that I may drink, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4967AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4967AI\"></sup>only let me pass through on foot,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>just as the sons of Esau who live in Seir and the Moabites who live in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4968AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4968AJ\"></sup>Ar did for me, until I cross over the Jordan into the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God is giving to us.’",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4969AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4969AK\"></sup>Sihon king of Heshbon was not willing for us to pass through his land; for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4969AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4969AL\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God hardened his spirit and made his heart obstinate, in order to deliver him into your hand, as <i>he is</i> today.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘See, I have begun to deliver Sihon and his land over to you. Begin to occupy, that you may possess his land.’",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“Then Sihon with all his people came out to meet us in battle at Jahaz.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4972AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4972AM\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God delivered him over to us, and we <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4972AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4972AN\"></sup>defeated him with his sons and all his people.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>So we captured all his cities at that time and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4973AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4973AO\"></sup>utterly destroyed the men, women and children of every city. We left no survivor.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>We took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4974AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4974AP\"></sup>only the animals as our booty and the spoil of the cities which we had captured.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>From <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4975AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4975AQ\"></sup>Aroer which is on the edge of the valley of Arnon and <i>from</i> the city which is in the valley, even to Gilead, there was no city that was too high for us; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God delivered all over to us.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4976AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4976AR\"></sup>Only you did not go near to the land of the sons of Ammon, all along the river <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4976AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4976AS\"></sup>Jabbok and the cities of the hill country, and wherever the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God had commanded us."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4977A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4977A\"></sup>Then we turned and went up the road to Bashan, and Og, king of Bashan, with all his people came out to meet us in battle at Edrei.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘Do not fear him, for I have delivered him and all his people and his land into your hand; and you shall do to him just as you did to Sihon king of the Amorites, who lived at Heshbon.’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God delivered Og also, king of Bashan, with all his people into our hand, and we smote them until no survivor was left.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>We captured all his cities at that time; there was not a city which we did not take from them: sixty cities, all the region of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4980B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4980B\"></sup>Argob, the kingdom of Og in Bashan.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>All these were cities fortified with high walls, gates and bars, besides a great many unwalled towns.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>We utterly destroyed them, as we did to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4982C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4982C\"></sup>Sihon king of Heshbon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4982D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4982D\"></sup>utterly destroying the men, women and children of every city.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4983E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4983E\"></sup>But all the animals and the spoil of the cities we took as our booty.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4984F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4984F\"></sup>Thus we took the land at that time from the hand of the two kings of the Amorites who were beyond the Jordan, from the valley of Arnon to Mount Hermon",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>(Sidonians <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4985G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4985G\"></sup>call Hermon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4985H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4985H\"></sup>Sirion, and the Amorites call it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4985I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4985I\"></sup>Senir):",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>all the cities of the plateau and all Gilead and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4986J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4986J\"></sup>all Bashan, as far as Salecah and Edrei, cities of the kingdom of Og in Bashan.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>(For only Og king of Bashan was left of the remnant of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4987K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4987K\"></sup>Rephaim. Behold, his bedstead was an iron bedstead; it is in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4987L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4987L\"></sup>Rabbah of the sons of Ammon. Its length was nine cubits and its width four cubits by ordinary cubit.)",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“So we took possession of this land at that time. From <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4988M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4988M\"></sup>Aroer, which is by the valley of Arnon, and half the hill country of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4988N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4988N\"></sup>Gilead and its cities I gave to the Reubenites and to the Gadites.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The rest of Gilead and all Bashan, the kingdom of Og, I gave to the half-tribe of Manasseh, all the region of Argob (concerning all Bashan, it is called the land of Rephaim.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4990O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4990O\"></sup>Jair the son of Manasseh took all the region of Argob as far as the border of the Geshurites and the Maacathites, and called it, <i>that is</i>, Bashan, after his own name, Havvoth-jair, <i>as it is</i> to this day.)",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4991P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4991P\"></sup>To Machir I gave Gilead.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>To the Reubenites and to the Gadites I gave from Gilead even as far as the valley of Arnon, the middle of the valley as a border and as far as the river <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4992Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4992Q\"></sup>Jabbok, the border of the sons of Ammon;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the Arabah also, with the Jordan as <i>a</i> border, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4993R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4993R\"></sup>Chinnereth <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4993S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4993S\"></sup>even as far as the sea of the Arabah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4993T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4993T\"></sup>the Salt Sea, at the foot of the slopes of Pisgah on the east.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Then I commanded you at that time, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4994U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4994U\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given you this land to possess it; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4994V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4994V\"></sup>all you valiant men shall cross over armed before your brothers, the sons of Israel.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4995W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4995W\"></sup>But your wives and your little ones and your livestock (I know that you have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4995X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4995X\"></sup>much livestock) shall remain in your cities which I have given you,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4996Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4996Y\"></sup>until the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gives rest to your fellow countrymen as to you, and they also possess the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will give them beyond the Jordan. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4996Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4996Z\"></sup>Then you may return every man to his possession which I have given you.’",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>I commanded Joshua at that time, saying, ‘Your eyes have seen all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has done to these two kings; so the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall do to all the kingdoms into which you are about to cross.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Do not fear them, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4998AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4998AA\"></sup>is the one fighting for you.’",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“I also pleaded with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at that time, saying,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>‘O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, You have begun to show Your servant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5000AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5000AB\"></sup>Your greatness and Your strong hand; for what <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5000AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5000AC\"></sup>god is there in heaven or on earth who can do such works and mighty acts as Yours?",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Let me, I pray, cross over and see the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5001AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5001AD\"></sup>fair land that is beyond the Jordan, that good hill country and Lebanon.’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5002AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5002AE\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was angry with me on your account, and would not listen to me; and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘Enough! Speak to Me no more of this matter.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Go up to the top of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5003AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5003AF\"></sup>Pisgah and lift up your eyes to the west and north and south and east, and see <i>it</i> with your eyes, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5003AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5003AG\"></sup>for you shall not cross over this Jordan.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5004AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5004AH\"></sup>But charge Joshua and encourage him and strengthen him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5004AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5004AI\"></sup>for he shall go across at the head of this people, and he will give them as an inheritance the land which you will see.’",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So we remained in the valley opposite <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5005AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5005AJ\"></sup>Beth-peor."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>“Now, O Israel, listen to the statutes and the judgments which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5006A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5006A\"></sup>I am teaching you to perform, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5006B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5006B\"></sup>you may live and go in and take possession of the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, is giving you.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5007C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5007C\"></sup>You shall not add to the word which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5007D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5007D\"></sup>I am commanding you, nor take away from it, that you may keep the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God which I command you.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5008E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5008E\"></sup>Your eyes have seen what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has done in the case of Baal-peor, for all the men who followed Baal-peor, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has destroyed them from among you.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But you who held fast to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God are alive today, every one of you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“See, I have taught you statutes and judgments <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5010F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5010F\"></sup>just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God commanded me, that you should do thus in the land where you are entering to possess it.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So keep and do <i>them</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5011G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5011G\"></sup>for that is your wisdom and your understanding in the sight of the peoples who will hear all these statutes and say, ‘Surely this great nation is a wise and understanding people.’",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5012H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5012H\"></sup>what great nation is there that has a god <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5012I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5012I\"></sup>so near to it as is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5012J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5012J\"></sup>whenever we call on Him?",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Or what great nation is there that has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5013K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5013K\"></sup>statutes and judgments as righteous as this whole law which I am setting before you today?",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5014L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5014L\"></sup>give heed to yourself and keep your soul diligently, so that you do not forget the things which your eyes have seen and they do not depart from your heart <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5014M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5014M\"></sup>all the days of your life; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5014N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5014N\"></sup>make them known to your sons and your grandsons.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><i>Remember</i> the day you stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God at Horeb, when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘Assemble the people to Me, that I may let them hear My words <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5015O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5015O\"></sup>so they may learn to fear Me all the days they live on the earth, and that they may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5015P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5015P\"></sup>teach their children.’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You came near and stood at the foot of the mountain, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5016Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5016Q\"></sup>and the mountain burned with fire to the <i>very</i> heart of the heavens: darkness, cloud and thick gloom.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to you from the midst of the fire; you heard the sound of words, but you saw no form—only a voice.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So He declared to you His covenant which He commanded you to perform, <i>that is</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5018R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5018R\"></sup>the Ten Commandments; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5018S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5018S\"></sup>He wrote them on two tablets of stone.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded me at that time to teach you statutes and judgments, that you might perform them in the land where you are going over to possess it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5020T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5020T\"></sup>watch yourselves carefully, since you did not see any <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5020U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5020U\"></sup>form on the day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to you at Horeb from the midst of the fire,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>so that you do not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5021V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5021V\"></sup>act corruptly and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5021W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5021W\"></sup>make a graven image for yourselves in the form of any figure, the likeness of male or female,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the likeness of any animal that is on the earth, the likeness of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5022X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5022X\"></sup>any winged bird that flies in the sky,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the likeness of anything that creeps on the ground, the likeness of any fish that is in the water below the earth.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And <i>beware</i> not to lift up your eyes to heaven and see the sun and the moon and the stars, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5024Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5024Y\"></sup>all the host of heaven, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5024Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5024Z\"></sup>and be drawn away and worship them and serve them, those which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has allotted to all the peoples under the whole heaven.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has taken you and brought you out of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5025AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5025AA\"></sup>the iron furnace, from Egypt, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5025AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5025AB\"></sup>be a people for His own possession, as today.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5026AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5026AC\"></sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was angry with me on your account, and swore that I would not cross the Jordan, and that I would not enter the good land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you as an inheritance.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5027AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5027AD\"></sup>I will die in this land, I shall not cross the Jordan, but you shall cross and take possession of this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5027AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5027AE\"></sup>good land.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So watch yourselves, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5028AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5028AF\"></sup>that you do not forget the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God which He made with you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5028AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5028AG\"></sup>make for yourselves a graven image in the form of anything <i>against</i> which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has commanded you.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5029AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5029AH\"></sup>consuming fire, a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5029AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5029AI\"></sup>jealous God.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“When you become the father of children and children’s children and have remained long in the land, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5030AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5030AJ\"></sup>act corruptly, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5030AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5030AK\"></sup>make an idol in the form of anything, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5030AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5030AL\"></sup>do that which is evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <i>so as</i> to provoke Him to anger,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5031AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5031AM\"></sup>call heaven and earth to witness against you today, that you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5031AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5031AN\"></sup>surely perish quickly from the land where you are going over the Jordan to possess it. You shall not live long on it, but will be utterly destroyed.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5032AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5032AO\"></sup>scatter you among the peoples, and you will be left few in number among the nations where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> drives you.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5033AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5033AP\"></sup>There you will serve gods, the work of man’s hands, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5033AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5033AQ\"></sup>wood and stone, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5033AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5033AR\"></sup>which neither see nor hear nor eat nor smell.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5034AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5034AS\"></sup>But from there you will seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and you will find <i>Him</i> if you search for Him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5034AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5034AT\"></sup>with all your heart and all your soul.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5035AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5035AU\"></sup>are in distress and all these things have come upon you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5035AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5035AV\"></sup>in the latter days <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5035AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5035AW\"></sup>you will return to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and listen to His voice.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5036AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5036AX\"></sup>compassionate God; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5036AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5036AY\"></sup>He will not fail you nor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5036AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5036AZ\"></sup>destroy you nor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5036BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5036BA\"></sup>forget the covenant with your fathers which He swore to them.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“Indeed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5037BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5037BB\"></sup>ask now concerning the former days which were before you, since the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5037BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5037BC\"></sup>day that God created man on the earth, and <i>inquire</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5037BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5037BD\"></sup>from one end of the heavens to the other. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5037BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5037BE\"></sup>Has <i>anything</i> been done like this great thing, or has <i>anything</i> been heard like it?",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5038BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5038BF\"></sup>Has <i>any</i> people heard the voice of God speaking from the midst of the fire, as you have heard <i>it</i>, and survived?",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5039BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5039BG\"></sup>Or has a god tried to go to take for himself a nation from within <i>another</i> nation <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5039BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5039BH\"></sup>by trials, by signs and wonders and by war and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5039BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5039BI\"></sup>by a mighty hand and by an outstretched arm and by great terrors, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God did for you in Egypt before your eyes?",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>To you it was shown that you might know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, He is God; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5040BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5040BJ\"></sup>there is no other besides Him.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5041BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5041BK\"></sup>Out of the heavens He let you hear His voice <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5041BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5041BL\"></sup>to discipline you; and on earth He let you see His great fire, and you heard His words from the midst of the fire.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5042BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5042BM\"></sup>Because He loved your fathers, therefore He chose their descendants after them. And He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5042BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5042BN\"></sup>personally brought you from Egypt by His great power,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>driving out from before you nations greater and mightier than you, to bring you in <i>and</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5043BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5043BO\"></sup>to give you their land for an inheritance, as it is today.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Know therefore today, and take it to your heart, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5044BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5044BP\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, He is God in heaven above and on the earth below; there is no other.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5045BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5045BQ\"></sup>So you shall keep His statutes and His commandments which I am giving you today, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5045BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5045BR\"></sup>it may go well with you and with your children after you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5045BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5045BS\"></sup>that you may live long on the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you for all time.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5046BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5046BT\"></sup>Then Moses set apart three cities across the Jordan to the east,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>that a manslayer might flee there, who unintentionally slew his neighbor without having enmity toward him in time past; and by fleeing to one of these cities he might live:",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5048BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5048BU\"></sup>Bezer in the wilderness on the plateau for the Reubenites, and Ramoth in Gilead for the Gadites, and Golan in Bashan for the Manassites.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Now this is the law which Moses set before the sons of Israel;",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>these are the testimonies and the statutes and the ordinances which Moses spoke to the sons of Israel, when they came out from Egypt,",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>across the Jordan, in the valley <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5051BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5051BV\"></sup>opposite Beth-peor, in the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5051BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5051BW\"></sup>Sihon king of the Amorites who lived at Heshbon, whom Moses and the sons of Israel defeated when they came out from Egypt.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>They took possession of his land and the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5052BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5052BX\"></sup>Og king of Bashan, the two kings of the Amorites, <i>who were</i> across the Jordan to the east,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5053BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5053BY\"></sup>Aroer, which is on the edge of the valley of Arnon, even as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5053BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5053BZ\"></sup>Mount Sion (that is, Hermon),",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>with all the Arabah across the Jordan to the east, even as far as the sea of the Arabah, at the foot of the slopes of Pisgah."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>Then Moses summoned all Israel and said to them:“Hear, O Israel, the statutes and the ordinances which I am speaking today in your hearing, that you may learn them and observe them carefully.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5056A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5056A\"></sup>a covenant with us at Horeb.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5057B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5057B\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did not make this covenant with our fathers, but with us, <i>with</i> all those of us alive here today.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5058C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5058C\"></sup>face to face at the mountain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5058D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5058D\"></sup>from the midst of the fire,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><i>while</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5059E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5059E\"></sup>I was standing between the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and you at that time, to declare to you the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5059F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5059F\"></sup>for you were afraid because of the fire and did not go up the mountain. He said,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5060G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5060G\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5061H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5061H\"></sup>You shall have no other gods before Me.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5062I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5062I\"></sup>You shall not make for yourself an idol, <i>or</i> any likeness <i>of</i> what is in heaven above or on the earth beneath or in the water under the earth.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You shall not worship them or serve them; for I, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, am a jealous God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5063J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5063J\"></sup>visiting the iniquity of the fathers on the children, and on the third and the fourth <i>generations</i> of those who hate Me,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5064K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5064K\"></sup>showing lovingkindness to thousands, to those who love Me and keep My commandments.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5065L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5065L\"></sup>You shall not take the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in vain, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will not leave him unpunished who takes His name in vain.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5066M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5066M\"></sup>Observe the sabbath day to keep it holy, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God commanded you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Six days you shall labor and do all your work,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5068N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5068N\"></sup>the seventh day is a sabbath of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; <i>in it</i> you shall not do any work, you or your son or your daughter or your male servant or your female servant or your ox or your donkey or any of your cattle or your sojourner who stays with you, so that your male servant and your female servant may rest as well as you.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5069O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5069O\"></sup>You shall remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God brought you out of there by a mighty hand and by an outstretched arm; therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God commanded you to observe the sabbath day.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5070P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5070P\"></sup>Honor your father and your mother, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has commanded you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5070Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5070Q\"></sup>that your days may be prolonged and that it may go well with you on the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5071R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5071R\"></sup>You shall not murder.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5072S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5072S\"></sup>You shall not commit adultery.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5073T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5073T\"></sup>You shall not steal.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5074U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5074U\"></sup>You shall not bear false witness against your neighbor.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5075V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5075V\"></sup>You shall not covet your neighbor’s wife, and you shall not desire your neighbor’s house, his field or his male servant or his female servant, his ox or his donkey or anything that belongs to your neighbor.’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“These words the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to all your assembly at the mountain from the midst of the fire, <i>of</i> the cloud and <i>of</i> the thick gloom, with a great voice, and He added no more. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5076W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5076W\"></sup>He wrote them on two tablets of stone and gave them to me.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And when you heard the voice from the midst of the darkness, while the mountain was burning with fire, you came near to me, all the heads of your tribes and your elders.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>You said, ‘Behold, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God has shown us His glory and His greatness, and we have heard His voice from the midst of the fire; we have seen today that God speaks with man, yet he lives.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5079X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5079X\"></sup>Now then why should we die? For this great fire will consume us; if we hear the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God any longer, then we will die.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5080Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5080Y\"></sup>who is there of all flesh who has heard the voice of the living God speaking from the midst of the fire, as we <i>have</i>, and lived?",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Go near and hear all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God says; then speak to us all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God speaks to you, and we will hear and do <i>it</i>.’",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heard the voice of your words when you spoke to me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5082Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5082Z\"></sup>and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘I have heard the voice of the words of this people which they have spoken to you. They have done well in all that they have spoken.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5083AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5083AA\"></sup>Oh that they had such a heart in them, that they would fear Me and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5083AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5083AB\"></sup>keep all My commandments always, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5083AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5083AC\"></sup>it may be well with them and with their sons forever!",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Go, say to them, “Return to your tents.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5085AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5085AD\"></sup>But as for you, stand here by Me, that I may speak to you all the commandments and the statutes and the judgments which you shall teach them, that they may observe <i>them</i> in the land which I give them to possess.’",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So you shall observe to do just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has commanded you; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5086AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5086AE\"></sup>you shall not turn aside to the right or to the left.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5087AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5087AF\"></sup>You shall walk in all the way which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has commanded you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5087AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5087AG\"></sup>that you may live and that it may be well with you, and that you may prolong <i>your</i> days in the land which you will possess."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>“Now this is the commandment, the statutes and the judgments which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has commanded <i>me</i> to teach you, that you might do <i>them</i> in the land where you are going over to possess it,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>so that you and your son and your grandson might <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5089A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5089A\"></sup>fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, to keep all His statutes and His commandments which I command you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5089B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5089B\"></sup>all the days of your life, and that your days may be prolonged.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>O Israel, you should listen and be careful to do <i>it</i>, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5090C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5090C\"></sup>it may be well with you and that you may multiply greatly, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, has promised you, <i>in</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5090D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5090D\"></sup>a land flowing with milk and honey.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5091E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5091E\"></sup>Hear, O Israel! The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is our God, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5091F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5091F\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is one!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5092G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5092G\"></sup>You shall love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5092H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5092H\"></sup>with all your heart and with all your soul and with all your might.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5093I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5093I\"></sup>These words, which I am commanding you today, shall be on your heart.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5094J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5094J\"></sup>You shall teach them diligently to your sons and shall talk of them when you sit in your house and when you walk by the way and when you lie down and when you rise up.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5095K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5095K\"></sup>You shall bind them as a sign on your hand and they shall be as frontals on your forehead.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5096L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5096L\"></sup>You shall write them on the doorposts of your house and on your gates.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Then it shall come about when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God brings you into the land which He swore to your fathers, Abraham, Isaac and Jacob, to give you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5097M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5097M\"></sup>great and splendid cities which you did not build,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and houses full of all good things which you did not fill, and hewn cisterns which you did not dig, vineyards and olive trees which you did not plant, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5098N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5098N\"></sup>you eat and are satisfied,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>then watch yourself, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5099O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5099O\"></sup>you do not forget the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who brought you from the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5100P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5100P\"></sup>You shall fear <i>only</i> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; and you shall worship Him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5100Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5100Q\"></sup>swear by His name.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5101R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5101R\"></sup>You shall not follow other gods, any of the gods of the peoples who surround you,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in the midst of you is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5102S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5102S\"></sup>jealous God; otherwise the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will be kindled against you, and He will wipe you off the face of the earth.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5103T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5103T\"></sup>You shall not put the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God to the test, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5103U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5103U\"></sup>as you tested <i>Him</i> at Massah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5104V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5104V\"></sup>You should diligently keep the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and His testimonies and His statutes which He has commanded you.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You shall do what is right and good in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5105W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5105W\"></sup>it may be well with you and that you may go in and possess the good land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore to <i>give</i> your fathers,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>by driving out all your enemies from before you, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5107X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5107X\"></sup>When your son asks you in time to come, saying, ‘What <i>do</i> the testimonies and the statutes and the judgments <i>mean</i> which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God commanded you?’",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>then you shall say to your son, ‘We were slaves to Pharaoh in Egypt, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought us from Egypt with a mighty hand.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Moreover, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> showed great and distressing signs and wonders before our eyes against Egypt, Pharaoh and all his household;",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He brought us out from there in order to bring us in, to give us the land which He had sworn to our fathers.’",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded us to observe all these statutes, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5111Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5111Y\"></sup>to fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God for our good always and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5111Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5111Z\"></sup>for our survival, as <i>it is</i> today.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5112AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5112AA\"></sup>It will be righteousness for us if we are careful to observe all this commandment before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, just as He commanded us."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5113A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5113A\"></sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God brings you into the land where you are entering to possess it, and clears away many nations before you, the Hittites and the Girgashites and the Amorites and the Canaanites and the Perizzites and the Hivites and the Jebusites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5113B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5113B\"></sup>seven nations greater and stronger than you,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God delivers them before you and you defeat them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5114C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5114C\"></sup>then you shall utterly destroy them. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5114D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5114D\"></sup>You shall make no covenant with them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5114E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5114E\"></sup>and show no favor to them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Furthermore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5115F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5115F\"></sup>you shall not intermarry with them; you shall not give your daughters to their sons, nor shall you take their daughters for your sons.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For they will turn your sons away from following Me to serve other gods; then the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be kindled against you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5116G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5116G\"></sup>He will quickly destroy you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But thus you shall do to them: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5117H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5117H\"></sup>you shall tear down their altars, and smash their <i>sacred</i> pillars, and hew down their Asherim, and burn their graven images with fire.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5118I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5118I\"></sup>a holy people to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has chosen you to be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5118J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5118J\"></sup>a people for His own possession out of all the peoples who are on the face of the earth.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5119K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5119K\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did not set His love on you nor choose you because you were more in number than any of the peoples, for you were the fewest of all peoples,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>but because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> loved you and kept the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5120L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5120L\"></sup>oath which He swore to your forefathers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5120M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5120M\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought you out by a mighty hand and redeemed you from the house of slavery, from the hand of Pharaoh king of Egypt.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Know therefore that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5121N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5121N\"></sup>He is God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5121O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5121O\"></sup>the faithful God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5121P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5121P\"></sup>who keeps His covenant and His lovingkindness to a thousandth generation with those who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5121Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5121Q\"></sup>love Him and keep His commandments;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5122R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5122R\"></sup>repays those who hate Him to their faces, to destroy them; He will not delay with him who hates Him, He will repay him to his face.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Therefore, you shall keep the commandment and the statutes and the judgments which I am commanding you today, to do them.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5124S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5124S\"></sup>Then it shall come about, because you listen to these judgments and keep and do them, that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will keep with you His covenant and His lovingkindness which He swore to your forefathers.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5125T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5125T\"></sup>love you and bless you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5125U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5125U\"></sup>multiply you; He will also bless the fruit of your womb and the fruit of your ground, your grain and your new wine and your oil, the increase of your herd and the young of your flock, in the land which He swore to your forefathers to give you.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You shall be blessed above all peoples; there will be no male or female <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5126V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5126V\"></sup>barren among you or among your cattle.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5127W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5127W\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will remove from you all sickness; and He will not put on you any of the harmful diseases of Egypt which you have known, but He will lay them on all who hate you.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>You shall consume all the peoples whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will deliver to you; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5128X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5128X\"></sup>your eye shall not pity them, nor shall you serve their gods, for that <i>would be</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5128Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5128Y\"></sup>a snare to you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“If you should say in your heart, ‘These nations are greater than I; how can I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5129Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5129Z\"></sup>dispossess them?’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>you shall not be afraid of them; you shall well <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5130AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5130AA\"></sup>remember what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God did to Pharaoh and to all Egypt:",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5131AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5131AB\"></sup>the great trials which your eyes saw and the signs and the wonders and the mighty hand and the outstretched arm by which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God brought you out. So shall the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God do to all the peoples of whom you are afraid.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Moreover, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will send <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5132AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5132AC\"></sup>the hornet against them, until those who are left and hide themselves from you perish.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>You shall not dread them, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5133AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5133AD\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is in your midst, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5133AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5133AE\"></sup>a great and awesome God.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5134AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5134AF\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will clear away these nations before you little by little; you will not be able to put an end to them quickly, for the wild beasts would grow too numerous for you.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5135AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5135AG\"></sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will deliver them before you, and will throw them into great confusion until they are destroyed.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5136AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5136AH\"></sup>He will deliver their kings into your hand so that you will make their name perish from under heaven; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5136AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5136AI\"></sup>no man will be able to stand before you until you have destroyed them.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The graven images of their gods you are to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5137AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5137AJ\"></sup>burn with fire; you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5137AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5137AK\"></sup>not covet the silver or the gold that is on them, nor take it for yourselves, or you will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5137AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5137AL\"></sup>snared by it, for it is an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5137AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5137AM\"></sup>abomination to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>You shall not bring an abomination into your house, and like it come under the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5138AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5138AN\"></sup>ban; you shall utterly detest it and you shall utterly abhor it, for it is something banned."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>“All the commandments that I am commanding you today you shall be careful to do, that you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5139A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5139A\"></sup>may live and multiply, and go in and possess the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore <i>to give</i> to your forefathers.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5140B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5140B\"></sup>You shall remember all the way which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5140C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5140C\"></sup>led you in the wilderness these forty years, that He might humble you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5140D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5140D\"></sup>testing you, to know what was in your heart, whether you would keep His commandments or not.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He humbled you and let you be hungry, and fed you with manna which you did not know, nor did your fathers know, that He might make you understand that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5141E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5141E\"></sup>man does not live by bread alone, but man lives by everything that proceeds out of the mouth of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5142F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5142F\"></sup>Your clothing did not wear out on you, nor did your foot swell these forty years.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5143G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5143G\"></sup>Thus you are to know in your heart that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God was disciplining you just as a man disciplines his son.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Therefore, you shall keep the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, to walk in His ways and to fear Him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5145H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5145H\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is bringing you into a good land, a land of brooks of water, of fountains and springs, flowing forth in valleys and hills;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>a land of wheat and barley, of vines and fig trees and pomegranates, a land of olive oil and honey;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>a land where you will eat food without scarcity, in which you will not lack anything; a land whose stones are iron, and out of whose hills you can dig copper.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5148I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5148I\"></sup>you have eaten and are satisfied, you shall bless the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God for the good land which He has given you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Beware that you do not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5149J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5149J\"></sup>forget the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God by not keeping His commandments and His ordinances and His statutes which I am commanding you today;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>otherwise, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5150K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5150K\"></sup>when you have eaten and are satisfied, and have built good houses and lived <i>in them</i>,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and when your herds and your flocks multiply, and your silver and gold multiply, and all that you have multiplies,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>then your heart will become proud and you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5152L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5152L\"></sup>forget the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God who brought you out from the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He led you through <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5153M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5153M\"></sup>the great and terrible wilderness, <i>with its</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5153N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5153N\"></sup>fiery serpents and scorpions and thirsty ground where there was no water; He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5153O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5153O\"></sup>brought water for you out of the rock of flint.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>In the wilderness He fed you manna <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5154P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5154P\"></sup>which your fathers did not know, that He might humble you and that He might <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5154Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5154Q\"></sup>test you, to do good for you in the end.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Otherwise, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5155R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5155R\"></sup>you may say in your heart, ‘My power and the strength of my hand made me this wealth.’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But you shall remember the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5156S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5156S\"></sup>it is He who is giving you power to make wealth, that He may confirm His covenant which He swore to your fathers, as <i>it is</i> this day.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>It shall come about if you ever forget the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and go after other gods and serve them and worship them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5157T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5157T\"></sup>I testify against you today that you will surely perish.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Like the nations that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> makes to perish before you, so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5158U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5158U\"></sup>you shall perish; because you would not listen to the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>“Hear, O Israel! You are crossing over the Jordan today to go in to dispossess <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5159A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5159A\"></sup>nations greater and mightier than you, great cities <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5159B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5159B\"></sup>fortified to heaven,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>a people great and tall, the sons of the Anakim, whom you know and of whom you have heard <i>it said</i>, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5160C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5160C\"></sup>Who can stand before the sons of Anak?’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Know therefore today that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5161D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5161D\"></sup>it is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God who is crossing over before you as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5161E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5161E\"></sup>a consuming fire. He will destroy them and He will subdue them before you, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5161F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5161F\"></sup>you may drive them out and destroy them quickly, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken to you.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5162G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5162G\"></sup>Do not say in your heart when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has driven them out before you, ‘Because of my righteousness the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has brought me in to possess this land,’ but <i>it is</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5162H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5162H\"></sup>because of the wickedness of these nations <i>that</i> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is dispossessing them before you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>It is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5163I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5163I\"></sup>not for your righteousness or for the uprightness of your heart that you are going to possess their land, but <i>it is</i> because of the wickedness of these nations <i>that</i> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is driving them out before you, in order to confirm <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5163J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5163J\"></sup>the oath which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore to your fathers, to Abraham, Isaac and Jacob.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Know, then, <i>it is</i> not because of your righteousness <i>that</i> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you this good land to possess, for you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5164K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5164K\"></sup>a stubborn people.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Remember, do not forget how you provoked the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God to wrath in the wilderness; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5165L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5165L\"></sup>from the day that you left the land of Egypt until you arrived at this place, you have been rebellious against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Even <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5166M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5166M\"></sup>at Horeb you provoked the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to wrath, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was so angry with you that He would have destroyed you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When I went up to the mountain to receive the tablets of stone, the tablets of the covenant which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had made with you, then I remained on the mountain forty days and nights; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5167N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5167N\"></sup>I neither ate bread nor drank water.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave me the two tablets of stone <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5168O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5168O\"></sup>written by the finger of God; and on them <i>were</i> all the words which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken with you at the mountain from the midst of the fire on the day of the assembly.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>It came about <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5169P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5169P\"></sup>at the end of forty days and nights that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave me the two tablets of stone, the tablets of the covenant.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5170Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5170Q\"></sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘Arise, go down from here quickly, for your people whom you brought out of Egypt have acted corruptly. They have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5170R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5170R\"></sup>quickly turned aside from the way which I commanded them; they have made a molten image for themselves.’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5171S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5171S\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke further to me, saying, ‘I have seen this people, and indeed, it is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5171T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5171T\"></sup>stubborn people.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5172U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5172U\"></sup>Let Me alone, that I may destroy them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5172V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5172V\"></sup>blot out their name from under heaven; and I will make of you a nation mightier and greater than they.’",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5173W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5173W\"></sup>So I turned and came down from the mountain while the mountain was burning with fire, and the two tablets of the covenant were in my two hands.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And I saw that you had indeed sinned against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. You had made for yourselves a molten calf; you had turned aside quickly from the way which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I took hold of the two tablets and threw them from my hands and smashed them before your eyes.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5176X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5176X\"></sup>I fell down before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5176Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5176Y\"></sup>as at the first, forty days and nights; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5176Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5176Z\"></sup>I neither ate bread nor drank water, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5176AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5176AA\"></sup>because of all your sin which you had committed in doing what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to provoke Him to anger.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5177AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5177AB\"></sup>I was afraid of the anger and hot displeasure with which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was wrathful against you in order to destroy you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5177AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5177AC\"></sup>but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> listened to me that time also.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was angry enough with Aaron to destroy him; so I also prayed for Aaron at the same time.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5179AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5179AD\"></sup>I took your sinful <i>thing</i>, the calf which you had made, and burned it with fire and crushed it, grinding it very small until it was as fine as dust; and I threw its dust into the brook that came down from the mountain.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“Again at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5180AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5180AE\"></sup>Taberah and at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5180AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5180AF\"></sup>Massah and at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5180AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5180AG\"></sup>Kibroth-hattaavah you provoked the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to wrath.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent you from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5181AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5181AH\"></sup>Kadesh-barnea, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5181AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5181AI\"></sup>Go up and possess the land which I have given you,’ then you rebelled against the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5181AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5181AJ\"></sup>you neither believed Him nor listened to His voice.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5182AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5182AK\"></sup>You have been rebellious against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from the day I knew you.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5183AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5183AL\"></sup>So I fell down before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the forty days and nights, which I did because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said He would destroy you.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5184AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5184AM\"></sup>I prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, ‘O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, do not destroy Your people, even Your inheritance, whom You have redeemed through Your greatness, whom You have brought out of Egypt with a mighty hand.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Remember Your servants, Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob; do not look at the stubbornness of this people or at their wickedness or their sin.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Otherwise the land from which You brought us may say, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5186AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5186AN\"></sup>Because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was not able to bring them into the land which He had promised them and because He hated them He has brought them out to slay them in the wilderness.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Yet they are Your people, even <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5187AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5187AO\"></sup>Your inheritance, whom You have brought out by Your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5187AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5187AP\"></sup>great power and Your outstretched arm.’"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>“At that time the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5188A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5188A\"></sup>Cut out for yourself two tablets of stone like the former ones, and come up to Me on the mountain, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5188B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5188B\"></sup>make an ark of wood for yourself.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5189C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5189C\"></sup>I will write on the tablets the words that were on the former tablets which you shattered, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5189D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5189D\"></sup>you shall put them in the ark.’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5190E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5190E\"></sup>I made an ark of acacia wood and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5190F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5190F\"></sup>cut out two tablets of stone like the former ones, and went up on the mountain with the two tablets in my hand.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He wrote on the tablets, like the former writing, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5191G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5191G\"></sup>the Ten Commandments <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5191H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5191H\"></sup>which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken to you on the mountain from the midst of the fire <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5191I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5191I\"></sup>on the day of the assembly; and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave them to me.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then I turned and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5192J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5192J\"></sup>came down from the mountain and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5192K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5192K\"></sup>put the tablets in the ark which I had made; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5192L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5192L\"></sup>and there they are, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded me.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>(Now the sons of Israel set out from Beeroth <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5193M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5193M\"></sup>Bene-jaakan to Moserah. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5193N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5193N\"></sup>There Aaron died and there he was buried and Eleazar his son ministered as priest in his place.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5194O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5194O\"></sup>From there they set out to Gudgodah, and from Gudgodah to Jotbathah, a land of brooks of water.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5195P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5195P\"></sup>At that time the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> set apart the tribe of Levi to carry the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to stand before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5195Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5195Q\"></sup>to serve Him and to bless in His name until this day.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5196R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5196R\"></sup>Therefore, Levi does not have a portion or inheritance with his brothers; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is his inheritance, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God spoke to him.)",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5197S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5197S\"></sup>I, moreover, stayed on the mountain forty days and forty nights like the first time, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> listened to me that time also; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was not willing to destroy you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘Arise, proceed on your journey ahead of the people, that they may go in and possess the land which I swore to their fathers to give them.’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5199T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5199T\"></sup>Now, Israel, what does the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God require from you, but to fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, to walk in all His ways and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5199U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5199U\"></sup>love Him, and to serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5199V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5199V\"></sup>all your heart and with all your soul,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><i>and</i> to keep the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> commandments and His statutes which I am commanding you today for your good?",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5201W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5201W\"></sup>to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God belong heaven and the highest heavens, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5201X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5201X\"></sup>the earth and all that is in it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5202Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5202Y\"></sup>Yet on your fathers did the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> set His affection to love them, and He chose their descendants after them, <i>even</i> you above all peoples, as <i>it is</i> this day.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5203Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5203Z\"></sup>So circumcise your heart, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5203AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5203AA\"></sup>stiffen your neck no longer.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5204AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5204AB\"></sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is the God of gods and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5204AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5204AC\"></sup>Lord of lords, the great, the mighty, and the awesome God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5204AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5204AD\"></sup>who does not show partiality nor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5204AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5204AE\"></sup>take a bribe.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He executes justice for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5205AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5205AF\"></sup>the orphan and the widow, and shows His love for the alien by giving him food and clothing.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5206AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5206AG\"></sup>So show your love for the alien, for you were aliens in the land of Egypt.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You shall fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; you shall serve Him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5207AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5207AH\"></sup>cling to Him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5207AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5207AI\"></sup>you shall swear by His name.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5208AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5208AJ\"></sup>your praise and He is your God, who has done these great and awesome things for you which your eyes have seen.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5209AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5209AK\"></sup>Your fathers went down to Egypt seventy persons <i>in all</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5209AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5209AL\"></sup>and now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has made you as numerous as the stars of heaven."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>“You shall therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5210A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5210A\"></sup>love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and always <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5210B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5210B\"></sup>keep His charge, His statutes, His ordinances, and His commandments.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Know this day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5211C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5211C\"></sup>that I <i>am</i> not <i>speaking</i> with your sons who have not known and who have not seen the discipline of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God—His greatness, His mighty hand and His outstretched arm,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5212D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5212D\"></sup>His signs and His works which He did in the midst of Egypt to Pharaoh the king of Egypt and to all his land;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and what He did to Egypt’s army, to its horses and its chariots, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5213E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5213E\"></sup>when He made the water of the Red Sea to engulf them while they were pursuing you, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> completely destroyed them;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and what He did to you in the wilderness until you came to this place;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5215F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5215F\"></sup>what He did to Dathan and Abiram, the sons of Eliab, the son of Reuben, when the earth opened its mouth and swallowed them, their households, their tents, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5215G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5215G\"></sup>every living thing that followed them, among all Israel—",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>but your own eyes have seen all the great work of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which He did.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“You shall therefore keep every commandment which I am commanding you today, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5217H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5217H\"></sup>so that you may be strong and go in and possess the land into which you are about to cross to possess it;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5218I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5218I\"></sup>so that you may prolong <i>your</i> days on the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore to your fathers to give to them and to their descendants, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5218J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5218J\"></sup>a land flowing with milk and honey.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For the land, into which you are entering to possess it, is not like the land of Egypt from which you came, where you used to sow your seed and water it with your foot like a vegetable garden.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5220K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5220K\"></sup>the land into which you are about to cross to possess it, a land of hills and valleys, drinks water from the rain of heaven,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>a land for which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God cares; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5221L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5221L\"></sup>the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God are always on it, from the beginning even to the end of the year.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“It shall come about, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5222M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5222M\"></sup>if you listen obediently to my commandments which I am commanding you today, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5222N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5222N\"></sup>to love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and to serve Him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5222O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5222O\"></sup>with all your heart and all your soul,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5223P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5223P\"></sup>He will give the rain for your land in its season, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5223Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5223Q\"></sup>early and late rain, that you may gather in your grain and your new wine and your oil.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5224R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5224R\"></sup>He will give grass in your fields for your cattle, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5224S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5224S\"></sup>you will eat and be satisfied.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5225T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5225T\"></sup>Beware that your hearts are not deceived, and that you do not turn away and serve other gods and worship them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5226U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5226U\"></sup>the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be kindled against you, and He will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5226V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5226V\"></sup>shut up the heavens <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5226W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5226W\"></sup>so that there will be no rain and the ground will not yield its fruit; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5226X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5226X\"></sup>you will perish quickly from the good land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is giving you.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5227Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5227Y\"></sup>You shall therefore impress these words of mine on your heart and on your soul; and you shall bind them as a sign on your hand, and they shall be as frontals on your forehead.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5228Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5228Z\"></sup>You shall teach them to your sons, talking of them when you sit in your house and when you walk along the road and when you lie down and when you rise up.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5229AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5229AA\"></sup>You shall write them on the doorposts of your house and on your gates,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5230AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5230AB\"></sup>your days and the days of your sons may be multiplied on the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore to your fathers to give them, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5230AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5230AC\"></sup>long as the heavens <i>remain</i> above the earth.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For if you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5231AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5231AD\"></sup>careful to keep all this commandment which I am commanding you to do, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5231AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5231AE\"></sup>to love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, to walk in all His ways and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5231AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5231AF\"></sup>hold fast to Him,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5232AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5232AG\"></sup>drive out all these nations from before you, and you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5232AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5232AH\"></sup>dispossess nations greater and mightier than you.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5233AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5233AI\"></sup>Every place on which the sole of your foot treads shall be yours; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5233AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5233AJ\"></sup>your border will be from the wilderness to Lebanon, <i>and</i> from the river, the river Euphrates, as far as the western sea.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5234AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5234AK\"></sup>No man will be able to stand before you; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will lay the dread of you and the fear of you on all the land on which you set foot, as He has spoken to you.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5235AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5235AL\"></sup>See, I am setting before you today a blessing and a curse:",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5236AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5236AM\"></sup>blessing, if you listen to the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, which I am commanding you today;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5237AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5237AN\"></sup>curse, if you do not listen to the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, but turn aside from the way which I am commanding you today, by following other gods which you have not known.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“It shall come about, when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God brings you into the land where you are entering to possess it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5238AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5238AO\"></sup>that you shall place the blessing on Mount Gerizim and the curse on Mount Ebal.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Are they not across the Jordan, west of the way toward the sunset, in the land of the Canaanites who live in the Arabah, opposite <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5239AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5239AP\"></sup>Gilgal, beside <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5239AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5239AQ\"></sup>the oaks of Moreh?",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For you are about to cross the Jordan to go in to possess the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5240AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5240AR\"></sup>you shall possess it and live in it,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>and you shall be careful to do all the statutes and the judgments which I am setting before you today."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>“These are the statutes and the judgments which you shall carefully observe in the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, has given you to possess <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5242A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5242A\"></sup>as long as you live on the earth.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>You shall utterly destroy all the places where the nations whom you shall dispossess serve their gods, on the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5243B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5243B\"></sup>high mountains and on the hills and under every green tree.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5244C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5244C\"></sup>You shall tear down their altars and smash their <i>sacred</i> pillars and burn their Asherim with fire, and you shall cut down the engraved images of their gods and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5244D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5244D\"></sup>obliterate their name from that place.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You shall not act like this toward the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5246E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5246E\"></sup>But you shall seek <i>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span></i> at the place which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will choose from all your tribes, to establish His name there for His dwelling, and there you shall come.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>There you shall bring your burnt offerings, your sacrifices, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5247F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5247F\"></sup>your tithes, the contribution of your hand, your votive offerings, your freewill offerings, and the firstborn of your herd and of your flock.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>There also you and your households shall eat before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5248G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5248G\"></sup>rejoice in all your undertakings in which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has blessed you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“You shall not do at all what we are doing here today, every man <i>doing</i> whatever is right in his own eyes;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>for you have not as yet come to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5250H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5250H\"></sup>the resting place and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5250I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5250I\"></sup>inheritance which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When you cross the Jordan and live in the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you to inherit, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5251J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5251J\"></sup>He gives you rest from all your enemies around <i>you</i> so that you live in security,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5252K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5252K\"></sup>then it shall come about that the place in which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will choose for His name to dwell, there you shall bring all that I command you: your burnt offerings and your sacrifices, your tithes and the contribution of your hand, and all your choice votive offerings which you will vow to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5253L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5253L\"></sup>rejoice before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, you and your sons and daughters, your male and female servants, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5253M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5253M\"></sup>Levite who is within your gates, since <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5253N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5253N\"></sup>he has no portion or inheritance with you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5254O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5254O\"></sup>Be careful that you do not offer your burnt offerings in every <i>cultic</i> place you see,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>but in the place which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> chooses in one of your tribes, there you shall offer your burnt offerings, and there you shall do all that I command you.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5256P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5256P\"></sup>However, you may slaughter and eat meat within any of your gates, whatever you desire, according to the blessing of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God which He has given you; the unclean and the clean may eat of it, as of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5256Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5256Q\"></sup>the gazelle and the deer.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5257R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5257R\"></sup>Only you shall not eat the blood; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5257S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5257S\"></sup>you are to pour it out on the ground like water.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5258T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5258T\"></sup>You are not allowed to eat within your gates the tithe of your grain or new wine or oil, or the firstborn of your herd or flock, or any of your votive offerings which you vow, or your freewill offerings, or the contribution of your hand.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5259U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5259U\"></sup>you shall eat them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5259V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5259V\"></sup>the place which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will choose, you and your son and daughter, and your male and female servants, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5259W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5259W\"></sup>Levite who is within your gates; and you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5259X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5259X\"></sup>rejoice before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in all your undertakings.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5260Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5260Y\"></sup>Be careful that you do not forsake the Levite as long as you live in your land.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God extends your border <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5261Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5261Z\"></sup>as He has promised you, and you say, ‘I will eat meat,’ because you desire to eat meat, <i>then</i> you may eat meat, whatever you desire.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>If the place which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God chooses to put His name is too far from you, then you may slaughter of your herd and flock which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given you, as I have commanded you; and you may eat within your gates whatever you desire.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Just as a gazelle or a deer is eaten, so you will eat it; the unclean and the clean alike may eat of it.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Only be sure <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5264AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5264AA\"></sup>not to eat the blood, for the blood is the life, and you shall not eat the life with the flesh.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>You shall not eat it; you shall pour it out on the ground like water.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>You shall not eat it, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5266AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5266AB\"></sup>it may be well with you and your sons after you, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5266AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5266AC\"></sup>you will be doing what is right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5267AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5267AD\"></sup>Only your holy things which you may have and your votive offerings, you shall take and go to the place which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> chooses.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5268AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5268AE\"></sup>you shall offer your burnt offerings, the flesh and the blood, on the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; and the blood of your sacrifices shall be poured out on the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5268AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5268AF\"></sup>you shall eat the flesh.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“Be careful to listen to all these words which I command you, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5269AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5269AG\"></sup>it may be well with you and your sons after you forever, for you will be doing what is good and right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5270AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5270AH\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God cuts off before you the nations which you are going in to dispossess, and you dispossess them and dwell in their land,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>beware that you are not ensnared to follow them, after they are destroyed before you, and that you do not inquire after their gods, saying, ‘How do these nations serve their gods, that I also may do likewise?’",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5272AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5272AI\"></sup>You shall not behave thus toward the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, for every abominable act which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> hates they have done for their gods; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5272AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5272AJ\"></sup>they even burn their sons and daughters in the fire to their gods.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5273AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5273AK\"></sup>Whatever I command you, you shall be careful to do; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5273AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5273AL\"></sup>you shall not add to nor take away from it."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5274A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5274A\"></sup>If a prophet or a dreamer of dreams arises among you and gives you a sign or a wonder,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and the sign or the wonder comes true, concerning which he spoke to you, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5275B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5275B\"></sup>Let us go after other gods (whom you have not known) and let us serve them,’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>you shall not listen to the words of that prophet or that dreamer of dreams; for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5276C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5276C\"></sup>testing you to find out if <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5276D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5276D\"></sup>you love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God with all your heart and with all your soul.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5277E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5277E\"></sup>You shall follow the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and fear Him; and you shall keep His commandments, listen to His voice, serve Him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5277F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5277F\"></sup>cling to Him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But that prophet or that dreamer of dreams shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5278G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5278G\"></sup>put to death, because he has counseled rebellion against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God who brought you from the land of Egypt and redeemed you from the house of slavery, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5278H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5278H\"></sup>to seduce you from the way in which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God commanded you to walk. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5278I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5278I\"></sup>So you shall purge the evil from among you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5279J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5279J\"></sup>If your brother, your mother’s son, or your son or daughter, or the wife you cherish, or your friend who is as your own soul, entice you secretly, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5279K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5279K\"></sup>Let us go and serve other gods’ (whom neither you nor your fathers have known,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>of the gods of the peoples who are around you, near you or far from you, from one end of the earth to the other end),",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5281L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5281L\"></sup>you shall not yield to him or listen to him; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5281M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5281M\"></sup>and your eye shall not pity him, nor shall you spare or conceal him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5282N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5282N\"></sup>But you shall surely kill him; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5282O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5282O\"></sup>your hand shall be first against him to put him to death, and afterwards the hand of all the people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So you shall stone him to death because he has sought <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5283P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5283P\"></sup>to seduce you from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God who brought you out from the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5284Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5284Q\"></sup>all Israel will hear and be afraid, and will never again do such a wicked thing among you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“If you hear in one of your cities, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you to live in, <i>anyone</i> saying <i>that</i>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>some worthless men have gone out from among you and have seduced the inhabitants of their city, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5286R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5286R\"></sup>Let us go and serve other gods’ (whom you have not known),",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>then you shall investigate and search out and inquire thoroughly. If it is true <i>and</i> the matter established that this abomination has been done among you,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5288S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5288S\"></sup>you shall surely strike the inhabitants of that city with the edge of the sword, utterly destroying it and all that is in it and its cattle with the edge of the sword.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5289T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5289T\"></sup>Then you shall gather all its booty into the middle of its open square and burn the city and all its booty with fire as a whole burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; and it shall be a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5289U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5289U\"></sup>ruin forever. It shall never be rebuilt.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Nothing from that which is put under the ban shall cling to your hand, in order that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> may turn from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5290V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5290V\"></sup>His burning anger and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5290W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5290W\"></sup>show mercy to you, and have compassion on you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5290X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5290X\"></sup>make you increase, just <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5290Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5290Y\"></sup>as He has sworn to your fathers,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>if you will listen to the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, keeping all His commandments which I am commanding you today, and doing what is right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>“You are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5292A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5292A\"></sup>the sons of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5292B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5292B\"></sup>you shall not cut yourselves nor shave your forehead for the sake of the dead.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5293C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5293C\"></sup>a holy people to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has chosen you to be a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5293D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5293D\"></sup>people for His own possession out of all the peoples who are on the face of the earth.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5294E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5294E\"></sup>You shall not eat any detestable thing.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5295F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5295F\"></sup>These are the animals which you may eat: the ox, the sheep, the goat,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>the deer, the gazelle, the roebuck, the wild goat, the ibex, the antelope and the mountain sheep.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Any animal that divides the hoof and has the hoof split in two <i>and</i> chews the cud, among the animals, that you may eat.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Nevertheless, you are not to eat of these among those which chew the cud, or among those that divide the hoof in two: the camel and the rabbit and the shaphan, for though they chew the cud, they do not divide the hoof; they are unclean for you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The pig, because it divides the hoof but <i>does</i> not <i>chew</i> the cud, it is unclean for you. You shall not eat any of their flesh nor touch their carcasses.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“These you may eat of all that are in water: anything that has fins and scales you may eat,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>but anything that does not have fins and scales you shall not eat; it is unclean for you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“You may eat any clean bird.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5303G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5303G\"></sup>these are the ones which you shall not eat: the eagle and the vulture and the buzzard,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and the red kite, the falcon, and the kite in their kinds,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and every raven in its kind,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and the ostrich, the owl, the sea gull, and the hawk in their kinds,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the little owl, the great owl, the white owl,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the pelican, the carrion vulture, the cormorant,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the stork, and the heron in their kinds, and the hoopoe and the bat.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And all the teeming life with wings are unclean to you; they shall not be eaten.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You may eat any clean bird.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5312H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5312H\"></sup>You shall not eat anything which dies <i>of itself</i>. You may give it to the alien who is in your town, so that he may eat it, or you may sell it to a foreigner, for you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5312I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5312I\"></sup>a holy people to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5312J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5312J\"></sup>You shall not boil a young goat in its mother’s milk.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5313K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5313K\"></sup>shall surely tithe all the produce from what you sow, which comes out of the field every year.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>You shall eat in the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5314L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5314L\"></sup>at the place where He chooses to establish His name, the tithe of your grain, your new wine, your oil, and the firstborn of your herd and your flock, so that you may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5314M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5314M\"></sup>learn to fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God always.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>If the distance is so great for you that you are not able to bring <i>the tithe</i>, since the place where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God chooses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5315N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5315N\"></sup>to set His name is too far away from you when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God blesses you,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>then you shall exchange <i>it</i> for money, and bind the money in your hand and go to the place which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God chooses.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>You may spend the money for whatever your heart desires: for oxen, or sheep, or wine, or strong drink, or whatever your heart desires; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5317O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5317O\"></sup>there you shall eat in the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and rejoice, you and your household.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Also you shall not neglect <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5318P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5318P\"></sup>the Levite who is in your town, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5318Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5318Q\"></sup>for he has no portion or inheritance among you.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5319R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5319R\"></sup>At the end of every third year you shall bring out all the tithe of your produce in that year, and shall deposit <i>it</i> in your town.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The Levite, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5320S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5320S\"></sup>because he has no portion or inheritance among you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5320T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5320T\"></sup>the alien, the orphan and the widow who are in your town, shall come and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5320U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5320U\"></sup>eat and be satisfied, in order that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5320V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5320V\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God may bless you in all the work of your hand which you do."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5321A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5321A\"></sup>At the end of <i>every</i> seven years you shall grant a remission <i>of debts</i>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>This is the manner of remission: every creditor shall release what he has loaned to his neighbor; he shall not exact it of his neighbor and his brother, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> remission has been proclaimed.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5323B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5323B\"></sup>From a foreigner you may exact <i>it</i>, but your hand shall release whatever of yours is with your brother.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>However, there will be no poor among you, since <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5324C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5324C\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will surely bless you in the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you as an inheritance to possess,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>if only you listen obediently to the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, to observe carefully all this commandment which I am commanding you today.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5326D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5326D\"></sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will bless you as He has promised you, and you will lend to many nations, but you will not borrow; and you will rule over many nations, but they will not rule over you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“If there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5327E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5327E\"></sup>a poor man with you, one of your brothers, in any of your towns in your land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5327F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5327F\"></sup>you shall not harden your heart, nor close your hand from your poor brother;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5328G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5328G\"></sup>you shall freely open your hand to him, and shall generously lend him sufficient for his need <i>in</i> whatever he lacks.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Beware that there is no base thought in your heart, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5329H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5329H\"></sup>The seventh year, the year of remission, is near,’ and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5329I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5329I\"></sup>your eye is hostile toward your poor brother, and you give him nothing; then he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5329J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5329J\"></sup>may cry to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> against you, and it will be a sin in you.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You shall generously give to him, and your heart shall not be grieved when you give to him, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5330K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5330K\"></sup>for this thing the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will bless you in all your work and in all your undertakings.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5331L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5331L\"></sup>For the poor will never cease <i>to be</i> in the land; therefore I command you, saying, ‘You shall freely open your hand to your brother, to your needy and poor in your land.’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5332M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5332M\"></sup>If your kinsman, a Hebrew man or woman, is sold to you, then he shall serve you six years, but in the seventh year you shall set him free.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When you set him free, you shall not send him away empty-handed.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You shall furnish him liberally from your flock and from your threshing floor and from your wine vat; you shall give to him as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has blessed you.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You shall remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God redeemed you; therefore I command you this today.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>It shall come about <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5336N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5336N\"></sup>if he says to you, ‘I will not go out from you,’ because he loves you and your household, since he fares well with you;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>then you shall take an awl and pierce it through his ear into the door, and he shall be your servant forever. Also you shall do likewise to your maidservant.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“It shall not seem hard to you when you set him free, for he has given you six years <i>with</i> double the service of a hired man; so the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will bless you in whatever you do.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5339O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5339O\"></sup>You shall consecrate to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God all the firstborn males that are born of your herd and of your flock; you shall not work with the firstborn of your herd, nor shear the firstborn of your flock.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5340P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5340P\"></sup>You and your household shall eat it every year before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in the place which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> chooses.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5341Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5341Q\"></sup>But if it has any defect, <i>such as</i> lameness or blindness, <i>or</i> any serious defect, you shall not sacrifice it to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>You shall eat it within your gates; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5342R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5342R\"></sup>the unclean and the clean alike <i>may eat it</i>, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5342S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5342S\"></sup>a gazelle or a deer.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5343T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5343T\"></sup>you shall not eat its blood; you are to pour it out on the ground like water."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>“Observe <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5344A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5344A\"></sup>the month of Abib and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5344B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5344B\"></sup>celebrate the Passover to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, for in the month of Abib the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God brought you out of Egypt by night.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>You shall sacrifice the Passover to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God from the flock and the herd, in the place where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> chooses to establish His name.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5346C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5346C\"></sup>You shall not eat leavened bread with it; seven days you shall eat with it unleavened bread, the bread of affliction (for you came out of the land of Egypt in haste), so that you may remember <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5346D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5346D\"></sup>all the days of your life the day when you came out of the land of Egypt.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For seven days no leaven shall be seen with you in all your territory, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5347E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5347E\"></sup>none of the flesh which you sacrifice on the evening of the first day shall remain overnight until morning.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You are not allowed to sacrifice the Passover in any of your towns which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5349F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5349F\"></sup>at the place where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God chooses to establish His name, you shall sacrifice the Passover in the evening at sunset, at the time that you came out of Egypt.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5350G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5350G\"></sup>cook and eat <i>it</i> in the place which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God chooses. In the morning you are to return to your tents.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Six days you shall eat unleavened bread, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5351H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5351H\"></sup>on the seventh day there shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5351I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5351I\"></sup>a solemn assembly to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; you shall do no work <i>on it</i>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5352J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5352J\"></sup>You shall count seven weeks for yourself; you shall begin to count seven weeks from the time you begin to put the sickle to the standing grain.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then you shall celebrate the Feast of Weeks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God with a tribute of a freewill offering of your hand, which you shall give just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God blesses you;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5354K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5354K\"></sup>rejoice before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, you and your son and your daughter and your male and female servants and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5354L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5354L\"></sup>the Levite who is in your town, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5354M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5354M\"></sup>the stranger and the orphan and the widow who are in your midst, in the place where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God chooses to establish His name.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5355N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5355N\"></sup>You shall remember that you were a slave in Egypt, and you shall be careful to observe these statutes.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5356O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5356O\"></sup>You shall celebrate the Feast of Booths seven days after you have gathered in from your threshing floor and your wine vat;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5357P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5357P\"></sup>rejoice in your feast, you and your son and your daughter and your male and female servants and the Levite and the stranger and the orphan and the widow who are in your towns.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Seven days you shall celebrate a feast to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in the place which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> chooses, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will bless you in all your produce and in all the work of your hands, so that you will be altogether joyful.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5359Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5359Q\"></sup>Three times in a year all your males shall appear before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in the place which He chooses, at the Feast of Unleavened Bread and at the Feast of Weeks and at the Feast of Booths, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5359R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5359R\"></sup>they shall not appear before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> empty-handed.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Every man shall give as he is able, according to the blessing of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God which He has given you.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“You shall appoint for yourself judges and officers in all your towns which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you, according to your tribes, and they shall judge the people with righteous judgment.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5362S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5362S\"></sup>You shall not distort justice; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5362T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5362T\"></sup>you shall not be partial, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5362U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5362U\"></sup>you shall not take a bribe, for a bribe blinds the eyes of the wise and perverts the words of the righteous.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Justice, <i>and only</i> justice, you shall pursue, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5363V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5363V\"></sup>you may live and possess the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5364W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5364W\"></sup>You shall not plant for yourself an Asherah of any kind of tree beside the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, which you shall make for yourself.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5365X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5365X\"></sup>You shall not set up for yourself a <i>sacred</i> pillar which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God hates."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5366A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5366A\"></sup>You shall not sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God an ox or a sheep which has a blemish <i>or</i> any defect, for that is a detestable thing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5367B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5367B\"></sup>If there is found in your midst, in any of your towns, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you, a man or a woman who does what is evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, by transgressing His covenant,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and has gone and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5368C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5368C\"></sup>served other gods and worshiped them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5368D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5368D\"></sup>or the sun or the moon or any of the heavenly host, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5368E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5368E\"></sup>which I have not commanded,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and if it is told you and you have heard of it, then you shall inquire thoroughly. Behold, if it is true and the thing certain that this detestable thing has been done in Israel,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>then you shall bring out that man or that woman who has done this evil deed to your gates, <i>that is</i>, the man or the woman, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5370F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5370F\"></sup>you shall stone them to death.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5371G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5371G\"></sup>On the evidence of two witnesses or three witnesses, he who is to die shall be put to death; he shall not be put to death on the evidence of one witness.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5372H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5372H\"></sup>The hand of the witnesses shall be first against him to put him to death, and afterward the hand of all the people. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5372I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5372I\"></sup>So you shall purge the evil from your midst.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5373J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5373J\"></sup>If any case is too difficult for you to decide, between one kind of homicide or another, between one kind of lawsuit or another, and between one kind of assault or another, being cases of dispute in your courts, then you shall arise and go up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5373K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5373K\"></sup>the place which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God chooses.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So you shall come to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5374L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5374L\"></sup>the Levitical priest or the judge who is <i>in office</i> in those days, and you shall inquire <i>of them</i> and they will declare to you the verdict in the case.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You shall do according to the terms of the verdict which they declare to you from that place which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> chooses; and you shall be careful to observe according to all that they teach you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5376M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5376M\"></sup>According to the terms of the law which they teach you, and according to the verdict which they tell you, you shall do; you shall not turn aside from the word which they declare to you, to the right or the left.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The man who acts <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5377N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5377N\"></sup>presumptuously by not listening to the priest who stands there to serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, nor to the judge, that man shall die; thus you shall purge the evil from Israel.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then all the people will hear and be afraid, and will not act <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5378O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5378O\"></sup>presumptuously again.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“When you enter the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you, and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5379P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5379P\"></sup>possess it and live in it, and you say, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5379Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5379Q\"></sup>I will set a king over me like all the nations who are around me,’",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>you shall surely set a king over you whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God chooses, <i>one</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5380R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5380R\"></sup>from among your countrymen you shall set as king over yourselves; you may not put a foreigner over yourselves who is not your countryman.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5381S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5381S\"></sup>Moreover, he shall not multiply horses for himself, nor shall he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5381T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5381T\"></sup>cause the people to return to Egypt to multiply horses, since <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5381U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5381U\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has said to you, ‘You shall never again return that way.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5382V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5382V\"></sup>He shall not multiply wives for himself, or else his heart will turn away; nor shall he greatly increase silver and gold for himself.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Now it shall come about when he sits on the throne of his kingdom, he shall write for himself a copy of this law on a scroll <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5383W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5383W\"></sup>in the presence of the Levitical priests.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>It shall be with him and he shall read it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5384X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5384X\"></sup>all the days of his life, that he may learn to fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, by carefully observing all the words of this law and these statutes,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>that his heart may not be lifted up above his countrymen <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5385Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5385Y\"></sup>and that he may not turn aside from the commandment, to the right or the left, so that he and his sons may continue long in his kingdom in the midst of Israel."
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5386A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5386A\"></sup>The Levitical priests, the whole tribe of Levi, shall have no portion or inheritance with Israel; they shall eat the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> offerings by fire and His portion.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5387B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5387B\"></sup>They shall have no inheritance among their countrymen; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is their inheritance, as He promised them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5388C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5388C\"></sup>Now this shall be the priests’ due from the people, from those who offer a sacrifice, either an ox or a sheep, of which they shall give to the priest the shoulder and the two cheeks and the stomach.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You shall give him the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5389D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5389D\"></sup>first fruits of your grain, your new wine, and your oil, and the first shearing of your sheep.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5390E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5390E\"></sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has chosen him and his sons from all your tribes, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5390F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5390F\"></sup>stand and serve in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forever.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Now if a Levite comes from any of your towns throughout Israel where he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5391G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5391G\"></sup>resides, and comes whenever he desires to the place which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> chooses,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>then he shall serve in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, like all his fellow Levites who stand there before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5393H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5393H\"></sup>They shall eat equal portions, except <i>what they receive</i> from the sale of their fathers’ <i>estates</i>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“When you enter the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you, you shall not learn to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5394I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5394I\"></sup>imitate the detestable things of those nations.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>There shall not be found among you anyone <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5395J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5395J\"></sup>who makes his son or his daughter pass through the fire, one who uses divination, one <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5395K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5395K\"></sup>who practices witchcraft, or one who interprets omens, or a sorcerer,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>or one who casts a spell, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5396L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5396L\"></sup>or a medium, or a spiritist, or one who calls up the dead.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For whoever does these things is detestable to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5397M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5397M\"></sup>because of these detestable things the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will drive them out before you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5398N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5398N\"></sup>You shall be blameless before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For those nations, which you shall dispossess, listen to those who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5399O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5399O\"></sup>practice witchcraft and to diviners, but as for you, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has not allowed you <i>to do</i> so.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5400P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5400P\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will raise up for you a prophet like me from among you, from your countrymen, you shall listen to him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>This is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5401Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5401Q\"></sup>according to all that you asked of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in Horeb on the day of the assembly, saying, ‘Let me not hear again the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, let me not see this great fire anymore, or I will die.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5402R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5402R\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘They have spoken well.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I will raise up a prophet from among their countrymen like you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5403S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5403S\"></sup>I will put My words in his mouth, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5403T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5403T\"></sup>he shall speak to them all that I command him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5404U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5404U\"></sup>It shall come about that whoever will not listen to My words which he shall speak in My name, I Myself will require <i>it</i> of him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But the prophet who speaks a word <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5405V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5405V\"></sup>presumptuously in My name which I have not commanded him to speak, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5405W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5405W\"></sup>which he speaks in the name of other gods, that prophet shall die.’",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>You may say in your heart, ‘How will we know the word which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not spoken?’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5407X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5407X\"></sup>When a prophet speaks in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, if the thing does not come about or come true, that is the thing which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not spoken. The prophet has spoken it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5407Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5407Y\"></sup>presumptuously; you shall not be afraid of him."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5408A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5408A\"></sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God cuts off the nations, whose land the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you, and you dispossess them and settle in their cities and in their houses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5409B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5409B\"></sup>you shall set aside three cities for yourself in the midst of your land, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you to possess.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You shall prepare the roads for yourself, and divide into three parts the territory of your land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will give you as a possession, so that any manslayer may flee there.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5411C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5411C\"></sup>Now this is the case of the manslayer who may flee there and live: when he kills his friend unintentionally, not hating him previously—",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>as when <i>a man</i> goes into the forest with his friend to cut wood, and his hand swings the axe to cut down the tree, and the iron <i>head</i> slips off the handle and strikes his friend so that he dies—he may flee to one of these cities and live;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>otherwise the avenger of blood might pursue the manslayer in the heat of his anger, and overtake him, because the way is long, and take his life, though he was not deserving of death, since he had not hated him previously.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Therefore, I command you, saying, ‘You shall set aside three cities for yourself.’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“If the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5415D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5415D\"></sup>enlarges your territory, just as He has sworn to your fathers, and gives you all the land which He promised to give your fathers—",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>if you carefully observe all this commandment which I command you today, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5416E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5416E\"></sup>to love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and to walk in His ways always—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5416F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5416F\"></sup>then you shall add three more cities for yourself, besides these three.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So innocent blood will not be shed in the midst of your land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you as an inheritance, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5417G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5417G\"></sup>bloodguiltiness be on you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5418H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5418H\"></sup>if there is a man who hates his neighbor and lies in wait for him and rises up against him and strikes him so that he dies, and he flees to one of these cities,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>then the elders of his city shall send and take him from there and deliver him into the hand of the avenger of blood, that he may die.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5420I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5420I\"></sup>You shall not pity him, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5420J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5420J\"></sup>you shall purge the blood of the innocent from Israel, that it may go well with you.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5421K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5421K\"></sup>You shall not move your neighbor’s boundary mark, which the ancestors have set, in your inheritance which you will inherit in the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you to possess.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5422L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5422L\"></sup>A single witness shall not rise up against a man on account of any iniquity or any sin which he has committed; on the evidence of two or three witnesses a matter shall be confirmed.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5423M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5423M\"></sup>If a malicious witness rises up against a man to accuse him of wrongdoing,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>then both the men who have the dispute shall stand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5424N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5424N\"></sup>before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, before the priests and the judges who will be <i>in office</i> in those days.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The judges <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5425O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5425O\"></sup>shall investigate thoroughly, and if the witness is a false witness <i>and</i> he has accused his brother falsely,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5426P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5426P\"></sup>you shall do to him just as he had intended to do to his brother. Thus you shall purge the evil from among you.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5427Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5427Q\"></sup>The rest will hear and be afraid, and will never again do such an evil thing among you.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5428R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5428R\"></sup>you shall not show pity: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5428S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5428S\"></sup>life for life, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5428T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5428T\"></sup>eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, foot for foot."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>“When you go out to battle against your enemies and see <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5429A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5429A\"></sup>horses and chariots <i>and</i> people more numerous than you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5429B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5429B\"></sup>do not be afraid of them; for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who brought you up from the land of Egypt, is with you.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When you are approaching the battle, the priest shall come near and speak to the people.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He shall say to them, ‘Hear, O Israel, you are approaching the battle against your enemies today. Do not be fainthearted. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5431C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5431C\"></sup>Do not be afraid, or panic, or tremble before them,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5432D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5432D\"></sup>is the one who goes with you, to fight for you against your enemies, to save you.’",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The officers also shall speak to the people, saying, ‘Who is the man that has built a new house and has not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5433E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5433E\"></sup>dedicated it? Let him depart and return to his house, otherwise he might die in the battle and another man would dedicate it.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Who is the man that has planted a vineyard and has not begun to use its fruit? Let him depart and return to his house, otherwise he might die in the battle and another man would begin to use its fruit.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5435F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5435F\"></sup>And who is the man that is engaged to a woman and has not married her? Let him depart and return to his house, otherwise he might die in the battle and another man would marry her.’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the officers shall speak further to the people and say, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5436G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5436G\"></sup>Who is the man that is afraid and fainthearted? Let him depart and return to his house, so that he might not make his brothers’ hearts melt like his heart.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When the officers have finished speaking to the people, they shall appoint commanders of armies at the head of the people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“When you approach a city to fight against it, you shall offer it terms of peace.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>If it agrees to make peace with you and opens to you, then all the people who are found in it shall become your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5439H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5439H\"></sup>forced labor and shall serve you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>However, if it does not make peace with you, but makes war against you, then you shall besiege it.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives it into your hand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5441I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5441I\"></sup>you shall strike all the men in it with the edge of the sword.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Only the women and the children and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5442J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5442J\"></sup>the animals and all that is in the city, all its spoil, you shall take as booty for yourself; and you shall use the spoil of your enemies which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given you.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Thus you shall do to all the cities that are very far from you, which are not of the cities of these nations nearby.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5444K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5444K\"></sup>Only in the cities of these peoples that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you as an inheritance, you shall not leave alive anything that breathes.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But you shall utterly destroy them, the Hittite and the Amorite, the Canaanite and the Perizzite, the Hivite and the Jebusite, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has commanded you,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>so that they may not teach you to do <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5446L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5446L\"></sup>according to all their detestable things which they have done for their gods, so that you would <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5446M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5446M\"></sup>sin against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“When you besiege a city a long time, to make war against it in order to capture it, you shall not destroy its trees by swinging an axe against them; for you may eat from them, and you shall not cut them down. For is the tree of the field a man, that it should be besieged by you?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Only the trees which you know are not fruit trees you shall destroy and cut down, that you may construct siegeworks against the city that is making war with you until it falls."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>“If a slain person is found lying in the open country in the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you to possess, <i>and</i> it is not known who has struck him,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>then your elders and your judges shall go out and measure <i>the distance</i> to the cities which are around the slain one.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>It shall be that the city which is nearest to the slain man, that is, the elders of that city, shall take a heifer of the herd, which has not been worked and which has not pulled in a yoke;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and the elders of that city shall bring the heifer down to a valley with running water, which has not been plowed or sown, and shall break the heifer’s neck there in the valley.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5453A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5453A\"></sup>the priests, the sons of Levi, shall come near, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has chosen them to serve Him and to bless in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and every dispute and every assault shall be settled by them.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>All the elders of that city which is nearest to the slain man shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5454B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5454B\"></sup>wash their hands over the heifer whose neck was broken in the valley;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and they shall answer and say, ‘Our hands did not shed this blood, nor did our eyes see <i>it</i>.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Forgive Your people Israel whom You have redeemed, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and do not place the guilt of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5456C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5456C\"></sup>innocent blood in the midst of Your people Israel.’ And the bloodguiltiness shall be forgiven them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5457D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5457D\"></sup>So you shall remove the guilt of innocent blood from your midst, when you do what is right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“When you go out to battle against your enemies, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5458E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5458E\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God delivers them into your hands and you take them away captive,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and see among the captives a beautiful woman, and have a desire for her and would take her as a wife for yourself,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>then you shall bring her home to your house, and she shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5460F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5460F\"></sup>shave her head and trim her nails.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>She shall also remove the clothes of her captivity and shall remain in your house, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5461G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5461G\"></sup>mourn her father and mother a full month; and after that you may go in to her and be her husband and she shall be your wife.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>It shall be, if you are not pleased with her, then you shall let her go wherever she wishes; but you shall certainly not sell her for money, you shall not mistreat her, because you have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5462H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5462H\"></sup>humbled her.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“If a man has two wives, the one loved and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5463I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5463I\"></sup>the other unloved, and <i>both</i> the loved and the unloved have borne him sons, if the firstborn son belongs to the unloved,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>then it shall be in the day he wills what he has to his sons, he cannot make the son of the loved the firstborn before the son of the unloved, who is the firstborn.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But he shall acknowledge the firstborn, the son of the unloved, by giving him a double portion of all that he has, for he is the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5465J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5465J\"></sup>beginning of his strength; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5465K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5465K\"></sup>to him belongs the right of the firstborn.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“If any man has a stubborn and rebellious son who will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5466L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5466L\"></sup>not obey his father or his mother, and when they chastise him, he will not even listen to them,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>then his father and mother shall seize him, and bring him out to the elders of his city at the gateway of his hometown.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>They shall say to the elders of his city, ‘This son of ours is stubborn and rebellious, he will not obey us, he is a glutton and a drunkard.’",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5469M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5469M\"></sup>Then all the men of his city shall stone him to death; so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5469N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5469N\"></sup>you shall remove the evil from your midst, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5469O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5469O\"></sup>all Israel will hear <i>of it</i> and fear.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“If a man has committed a sin <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5470P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5470P\"></sup>worthy of death and he is put to death, and you hang him on a tree,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5471Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5471Q\"></sup>his corpse shall not hang all night on the tree, but you shall surely bury him on the same day (for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5471R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5471R\"></sup>he who is hanged is accursed of God), so that you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5471S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5471S\"></sup>do not defile your land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you as an inheritance."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5472A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5472A\"></sup>You shall not see your countryman’s ox or his sheep straying away, and pay no attention to them; you shall certainly bring them back to your countryman.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>If your countryman is not near you, or if you do not know him, then you shall bring it home to your house, and it shall remain with you until your countryman looks for it; then you shall restore it to him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Thus you shall do with his donkey, and you shall do the same with his garment, and you shall do likewise with anything lost by your countryman, which he has lost and you have found. You are not allowed to neglect <i>them</i>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You shall not see your countryman’s donkey or his ox fallen down on the way, and pay no attention to them; you shall certainly help him to raise <i>them</i> up.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“A woman shall not wear man’s clothing, nor shall a man put on a woman’s clothing; for whoever does these things is an abomination to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“If you happen to come upon a bird’s nest along the way, in any tree or on the ground, with young ones or eggs, and the mother sitting on the young or on the eggs, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5477B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5477B\"></sup>you shall not take the mother with the young;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>you shall certainly let the mother go, but the young you may take for yourself, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5478C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5478C\"></sup>in order that it may be well with you and that you may prolong your days.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“When you build a new house, you shall make a parapet for your roof, so that you will not bring bloodguilt on your house if anyone falls from it.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5480D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5480D\"></sup>You shall not sow your vineyard with two kinds of seed, or all the produce of the seed which you have sown and the increase of the vineyard will become defiled.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5481E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5481E\"></sup>You shall not plow with an ox and a donkey together.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5482F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5482F\"></sup>You shall not wear a material mixed of wool and linen together.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5483G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5483G\"></sup>You shall make yourself tassels on the four corners of your garment with which you cover yourself.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5484H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5484H\"></sup>If any man takes a wife and goes in to her and <i>then</i> turns against her,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and charges her with shameful deeds and publicly defames her, and says, ‘I took this woman, <i>but</i> when I came near her, I did not find her a virgin,’",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>then the girl’s father and her mother shall take and bring out the <i>evidence</i> of the girl’s virginity to the elders of the city at the gate.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The girl’s father shall say to the elders, ‘I gave my daughter to this man for a wife, but he turned against her;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and behold, he has charged her with shameful deeds, saying, “I did not find your daughter a virgin.” But this is the evidence of my daughter’s virginity.’ And they shall spread the garment before the elders of the city.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5489I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5489I\"></sup>the elders of that city shall take the man and chastise him,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and they shall fine him a hundred <i>shekels</i> of silver and give it to the girl’s father, because he publicly defamed a virgin of Israel. And she shall remain his wife; he cannot divorce her all his days.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“But if this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5491J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5491J\"></sup>charge is true, that the girl was not found a virgin,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>then they shall bring out the girl to the doorway of her father’s house, and the men of her city shall stone her to death because she has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5492K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5492K\"></sup>committed an act of folly in Israel by playing the harlot in her father’s house; thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5492L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5492L\"></sup>you shall purge the evil from among you.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5493M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5493M\"></sup>If a man is found lying with a married woman, then both of them shall die, the man who lay with the woman, and the woman; thus you shall purge the evil from Israel.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5494N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5494N\"></sup>If there is a girl who is a virgin engaged to a man, and <i>another</i> man finds her in the city and lies with her,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>then you shall bring them both out to the gate of that city and you shall stone them to death; the girl, because she did not cry out in the city, and the man, because he has violated his neighbor’s wife. Thus you shall purge the evil from among you.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“But if in the field the man finds the girl who is engaged, and the man forces her and lies with her, then only the man who lies with her shall die.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But you shall do nothing to the girl; there is no sin in the girl worthy of death, for just as a man rises against his neighbor and murders him, so is this case.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When he found her in the field, the engaged girl cried out, but there was no one to save her.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5499O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5499O\"></sup>If a man finds a girl who is a virgin, who is not engaged, and seizes her and lies with her and they are discovered,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>then the man who lay with her shall give to the girl’s father fifty <i>shekels</i> of silver, and she shall become his wife because he has violated her; he cannot divorce her all his days.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5501P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5501P\"></sup>A man shall not take his father’s wife so that he will not uncover his father’s skirt."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5502A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5502A\"></sup>No one who is emasculated or has his male organ cut off shall enter the assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>No one of illegitimate birth shall enter the assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; none of his <i>descendants</i>, even to the tenth generation, shall enter the assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5504B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5504B\"></sup>No Ammonite or Moabite shall enter the assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; none of their <i>descendants</i>, even to the tenth generation, shall ever enter the assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5505C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5505C\"></sup>because they did not meet you with food and water on the way when you came out of Egypt, and because they hired against you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5505D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5505D\"></sup>Balaam the son of Beor from Pethor of Mesopotamia, to curse you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Nevertheless, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God was not willing to listen to Balaam, but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5506E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5506E\"></sup>turned the curse into a blessing for you because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5506F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5506F\"></sup>loves you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5507G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5507G\"></sup>You shall never seek their peace or their prosperity all your days.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“You shall not detest an Edomite, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5508H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5508H\"></sup>he is your brother; you shall not detest an Egyptian, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5508I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5508I\"></sup>because you were an alien in his land.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The sons of the third generation who are born to them may enter the assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“When you go out as an army against your enemies, you shall keep yourself from every evil thing.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5511J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5511J\"></sup>If there is among you any man who is unclean because of a nocturnal emission, then he must go outside the camp; he may not reenter the camp.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But it shall be when evening approaches, he shall bathe himself with water, and at sundown he may reenter the camp.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“You shall also have a place outside the camp and go out there,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and you shall have a spade among your tools, and it shall be when you sit down outside, you shall dig with it and shall turn to cover up your excrement.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Since <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5515K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5515K\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God walks in the midst of your camp to deliver you and to defeat your enemies before you, therefore your camp must be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5515L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5515L\"></sup>holy; and He must not see anything indecent among you or He will turn away from you.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5516M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5516M\"></sup>You shall not hand over to his master a slave who has escaped from his master to you.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He shall live with you in your midst, in the place which he shall choose in one of your towns where it pleases him; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5517N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5517N\"></sup>you shall not mistreat him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5518O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5518O\"></sup>None of the daughters of Israel shall be a cult prostitute, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5518P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5518P\"></sup>nor shall any of the sons of Israel be a cult prostitute.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You shall not bring the hire of a harlot or the wages of a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5519Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5519Q\"></sup>dog into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God for any votive offering, for both of these are an abomination to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5520R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5520R\"></sup>You shall not charge interest to your countrymen: interest on money, food, <i>or</i> anything that may be loaned at interest.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5521S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5521S\"></sup>You may charge interest to a foreigner, but to your countrymen you shall not charge interest, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5521T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5521T\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God may bless you in all that you undertake in the land which you are about to enter to possess.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5522U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5522U\"></sup>When you make a vow to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, you shall not delay to pay it, for it would be sin in you, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will surely require it of you.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>However, if you refrain from vowing, it would not be sin in you.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>You shall be careful to perform what goes out from your lips, just as you have voluntarily vowed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, what you have promised.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“When you enter your neighbor’s vineyard, then you may eat grapes until you are fully satisfied, but you shall not put any in your basket.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5526V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5526V\"></sup>When you enter your neighbor’s standing grain, then you may pluck the heads with your hand, but you shall not wield a sickle in your neighbor’s standing grain."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>“When a man takes a wife and marries her, and it happens that she finds no favor in his eyes because he has found some <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5527A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5527A\"></sup>indecency in her, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5527B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5527B\"></sup>he writes her a certificate of divorce and puts <i>it</i> in her hand and sends her out from his house,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and she leaves his house and goes and becomes another man’s <i>wife</i>,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and if the latter husband turns against her and writes her a certificate of divorce and puts <i>it</i> in her hand and sends her out of his house, or if the latter husband dies who took her to be his wife,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><i>then</i> her <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5530C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5530C\"></sup>former husband who sent her away is not allowed to take her again to be his wife, since she has been defiled; for that is an abomination before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and you shall not bring sin on the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you as an inheritance.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5531D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5531D\"></sup>When a man takes a new wife, he shall not go out with the army nor be charged with any duty; he shall be free at home one year and shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5531E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5531E\"></sup>give happiness to his wife whom he has taken.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“No one shall take a handmill or an upper millstone in pledge, for he would be taking a life in pledge.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5533F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5533F\"></sup>If a man is caught kidnapping any of his countrymen of the sons of Israel, and he deals with him violently or sells him, then that thief shall die; so you shall purge the evil from among you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5534G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5534G\"></sup>Be careful against an infection of leprosy, that you diligently observe and do according to all that the Levitical priests teach you; as I have commanded them, so you shall be careful to do.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Remember what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God did <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5535H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5535H\"></sup>to Miriam on the way as you came out of Egypt.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5536I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5536I\"></sup>When you make your neighbor a loan of any sort, you shall not enter his house to take his pledge.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You shall remain outside, and the man to whom you make the loan shall bring the pledge out to you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>If he is a poor man, you shall not sleep with his pledge.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5539J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5539J\"></sup>When the sun goes down you shall surely return the pledge to him, that he may sleep in his cloak and bless you; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5539K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5539K\"></sup>it will be righteousness for you before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5540L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5540L\"></sup>You shall not oppress a hired servant <i>who is</i> poor and needy, whether <i>he is</i> one of your countrymen or one of your aliens who is in your land in your towns.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5541M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5541M\"></sup>You shall give him his wages on his day before the sun sets, for he is poor and sets his heart on it; so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5541N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5541N\"></sup>he will not cry against you to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and it become sin in you.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5542O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5542O\"></sup>Fathers shall not be put to death for <i>their</i> sons, nor shall sons be put to death for <i>their</i> fathers; everyone shall be put to death for his own sin.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5543P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5543P\"></sup>You shall not pervert the justice due an alien <i>or</i> an orphan, nor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5543Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5543Q\"></sup>take a widow’s garment in pledge.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But you shall remember that you were a slave in Egypt, and that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God redeemed you from there; therefore I am commanding you to do this thing.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5545R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5545R\"></sup>When you reap your harvest in your field and have forgotten a sheaf in the field, you shall not go back to get it; it shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5545S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5545S\"></sup>for the alien, for the orphan, and for the widow, in order that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5545T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5545T\"></sup>may bless you in all the work of your hands.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5546U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5546U\"></sup>When you beat your olive tree, you shall not go over the boughs again; it shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5546V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5546V\"></sup>for the alien, for the orphan, and for the widow.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“When you gather the grapes of your vineyard, you shall not go over it again; it shall be for the alien, for the orphan, and for the widow.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>You shall remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt; therefore I am commanding you to do this thing."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5549A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5549A\"></sup>If there is a dispute between men and they go to court, and the judges decide their case, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5549B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5549B\"></sup>and they justify the righteous and condemn the wicked,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>then it shall be if the wicked man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5550C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5550C\"></sup>deserves to be beaten, the judge shall then make him lie down and be beaten in his presence with the number of stripes according to his guilt.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5551D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5551D\"></sup>He may beat him forty times <i>but</i> no more, so that he does not beat him with many more stripes than these and your brother is not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5551E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5551E\"></sup>degraded in your eyes.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5552F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5552F\"></sup>You shall not muzzle the ox while he is threshing.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“When brothers live together and one of them dies and has no son, the wife of the deceased shall not be <i>married</i> outside <i>the family</i> to a strange man. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5553G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5553G\"></sup>Her husband’s brother shall go in to her and take her to himself as wife and perform the duty of a husband’s brother to her.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>It shall be that the firstborn whom she bears shall assume the name of his dead brother, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5554H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5554H\"></sup>his name will not be blotted out from Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5555I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5555I\"></sup>But if the man does not desire to take his brother’s wife, then his brother’s wife shall go up to the gate to the elders and say, ‘My husband’s brother refuses to establish a name for his brother in Israel; he is not willing to perform the duty of a husband’s brother to me.’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the elders of his city shall summon him and speak to him. And <i>if</i> he persists and says, ‘I do not desire to take her,’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5557J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5557J\"></sup>then his brother’s wife shall come to him in the sight of the elders, and pull his sandal off his foot and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5557K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5557K\"></sup>spit in his face; and she shall declare, ‘Thus it is done to the man who does not build up his brother’s house.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In Israel his name shall be called, ‘The house of him whose sandal is removed.’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“If <i>two</i> men, a man and his countryman, are struggling together, and the wife of one comes near to deliver her husband from the hand of the one who is striking him, and puts out her hand and seizes his genitals,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>then you shall cut off her hand; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5560L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5560L\"></sup>you shall not show pity.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5561M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5561M\"></sup>You shall not have in your bag differing weights, a large and a small.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You shall not have in your house differing measures, a large and a small.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You shall have a full and just weight; you shall have a full and just measure, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5563N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5563N\"></sup>that your days may be prolonged in the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5564O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5564O\"></sup>everyone who does these things, everyone who acts unjustly is an abomination to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5565P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5565P\"></sup>Remember what Amalek did to you along the way when you came out from Egypt,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>how he met you along the way and attacked among you all the stragglers at your rear when you were faint and weary; and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5566Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5566Q\"></sup>did not fear God.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Therefore it shall come about when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5567R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5567R\"></sup>rest from all your surrounding enemies, in the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you as an inheritance to possess, you shall blot out the memory of Amalek from under heaven; you must not forget."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>“Then it shall be, when you enter the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you as an inheritance, and you possess it and live in it,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>that you shall take some of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5569A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5569A\"></sup>the first of all the produce of the ground which you bring in from your land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you, and you shall put <i>it</i> in a basket and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5569B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5569B\"></sup>go to the place where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God chooses to establish His name.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You shall go to the priest who is in office at that time and say to him, ‘I declare this day to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God that I have entered the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore to our fathers to give us.’",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the priest shall take the basket from your hand and set it down before the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You shall answer and say before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5572C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5572C\"></sup>My father was a wandering Aramean, and he went down to Egypt and sojourned there, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5572D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5572D\"></sup>few in number; but there he became a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5572E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5572E\"></sup>great, mighty and populous nation.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5573F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5573F\"></sup>Egyptians treated us harshly and afflicted us, and imposed hard labor on us.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5574G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5574G\"></sup>we cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of our fathers, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heard our voice and saw our affliction and our toil and our oppression;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5575H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5575H\"></sup>and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought us out of Egypt with a mighty hand and an outstretched arm and with great terror and with signs and wonders;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and He has brought us to this place and has given us this land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5576I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5576I\"></sup>a land flowing with milk and honey.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now behold, I have brought the first of the produce of the ground <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5577J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5577J\"></sup>which You, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> have given me.’ And you shall set it down before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and worship before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5578K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5578K\"></sup>the Levite and the alien who is among you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5578L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5578L\"></sup>rejoice in all the good which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given you and your household.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5579M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5579M\"></sup>When you have finished paying all the tithe of your increase in the third year, the year of tithing, then you shall give it to the Levite, to the stranger, to the orphan and to the widow, that they may eat in your towns and be satisfied.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You shall say before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, ‘I have removed the sacred <i>portion</i> from <i>my</i> house, and also have given it to the Levite and the alien, the orphan and the widow, according to all Your commandments which You have commanded me; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5580N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5580N\"></sup>I have not transgressed or forgotten any of Your commandments.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I have not eaten of it while mourning, nor have I removed any of it while I was unclean, nor offered any of it to the dead. I have listened to the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God; I have done according to all that You have commanded me.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5582O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5582O\"></sup>Look down from Your holy habitation, from heaven, and bless Your people Israel, and the ground which You have given us, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5582P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5582P\"></sup>a land flowing with milk and honey, as You swore to our fathers.’",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“This day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God commands you to do these statutes and ordinances. You shall therefore be careful to do them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5583Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5583Q\"></sup>with all your heart and with all your soul.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5584R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5584R\"></sup>You have today declared the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to be your God, and that you would walk in His ways and keep His statutes, His commandments and His ordinances, and listen to His voice.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has today declared you to be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5585S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5585S\"></sup>His people, a treasured possession, as He promised you, and that you should keep all His commandments;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and that He will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5586T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5586T\"></sup>set you high above all nations which He has made, for praise, fame, and honor; and that you shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5586U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5586U\"></sup>a consecrated people to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, as He has spoken.”"
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>Then Moses and the elders of Israel charged the people, saying, “Keep all the commandments which I command you today.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5588A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5588A\"></sup>So it shall be on the day when you cross the Jordan to the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you, that you shall set up for yourself large stones and coat them with lime",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and write on them all the words of this law, when you cross over, so that you may enter the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5589B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5589B\"></sup>a land flowing with milk and honey, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, promised you.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So it shall be when you cross the Jordan, you shall set up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5590C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5590C\"></sup>on Mount Ebal, these stones, as I am commanding you today, and you shall coat them with lime.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Moreover, you shall build there an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, an altar of stones; you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5591D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5591D\"></sup>shall not wield an iron <i>tool</i> on them.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You shall build the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God of uncut stones, and you shall offer on it burnt offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and you shall sacrifice peace offerings and eat there, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5593E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5593E\"></sup>rejoice before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You shall write on the stones all the words of this law very distinctly.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Moses and the Levitical priests spoke to all Israel, saying, “Be silent and listen, O Israel! This day you have become a people for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You shall therefore obey the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and do His commandments and His statutes which I command you today.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Moses also charged the people on that day, saying,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“When you cross the Jordan, these shall stand on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5598F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5598F\"></sup>Mount Gerizim to bless the people: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5598G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5598G\"></sup>Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Joseph, and Benjamin.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>For the curse, these shall stand on Mount Ebal: Reuben, Gad, Asher, Zebulun, Dan, and Naphtali.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The Levites shall then answer and say to all the men of Israel with a loud voice,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>‘Cursed is the man who makes <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5601H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5601H\"></sup>an idol or a molten image, an abomination to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the work of the hands of the craftsman, and sets <i>it</i> up in secret.’ And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5601I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5601I\"></sup>all the people shall answer and say, ‘Amen.’",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5602J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5602J\"></sup>Cursed is he who dishonors his father or mother.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5603K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5603K\"></sup>Cursed is he who moves his neighbor’s boundary mark.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5604L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5604L\"></sup>Cursed is he who misleads a blind <i>person</i> on the road.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5605M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5605M\"></sup>Cursed is he who distorts the justice due an alien, orphan, and widow.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5606N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5606N\"></sup>Cursed is he who lies with his father’s wife, because he has uncovered his father’s skirt.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5607O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5607O\"></sup>Cursed is he who lies with any animal.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5608P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5608P\"></sup>Cursed is he who lies with his sister, the daughter of his father or of his mother.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5609Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5609Q\"></sup>Cursed is he who lies with his mother-in-law.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5610R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5610R\"></sup>Cursed is he who strikes his neighbor in secret.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5611S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5611S\"></sup>Cursed is he who accepts a bribe to strike down an innocent person.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5612T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5612T\"></sup>Cursed is he who does not confirm the words of this law by doing them.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’"
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5613A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5613A\"></sup>Now it shall be, if you diligently obey the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, being careful to do all His commandments which I command you today, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5613B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5613B\"></sup>will set you high above all the nations of the earth.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>All these blessings will come upon you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5614C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5614C\"></sup>overtake you if you obey the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God:",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Blessed <i>shall</i> you <i>be</i> in the city, and blessed <i>shall</i> you <i>be</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5615D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5615D\"></sup>in the country.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Blessed <i>shall be</i> the offspring of your body and the produce of your ground and the offspring of your beasts, the increase of your herd and the young of your flock.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Blessed <i>shall be</i> your basket and your kneading bowl.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Blessed <i>shall</i> you <i>be</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5618E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5618E\"></sup>when you come in, and blessed <i>shall</i> you <i>be</i> when you go out.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall cause your enemies who rise up against you to be defeated before you; they will come out against you one way and will flee before you seven ways.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will command the blessing upon you in your barns and in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5620F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5620F\"></sup>all that you put your hand to, and He will bless you in the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5621G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5621G\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will establish you as a holy people to Himself, as He swore to you, if you keep the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and walk in His ways.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So all the peoples of the earth will see that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5622H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5622H\"></sup>you are called by the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and they will be afraid of you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5623I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5623I\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will make you abound in prosperity, in the offspring of your body and in the offspring of your beast and in the produce of your ground, in the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore to your fathers to give you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will open for you His good storehouse, the heavens, to give rain to your land in its season and to bless all the work of your hand; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5624J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5624J\"></sup>you shall lend to many nations, but you shall not borrow.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5625K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5625K\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will make you the head and not the tail, and you only will be above, and you will not be underneath, if you listen to the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, which I charge you today, to observe <i>them</i> carefully,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5626L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5626L\"></sup>do not turn aside from any of the words which I command you today, to the right or to the left, to go after other gods to serve them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5627M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5627M\"></sup>But it shall come about, if you do not obey the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, to observe to do all His commandments and His statutes with which I charge you today, that all these curses will come upon you and overtake you:",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5628N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5628N\"></sup>Cursed <i>shall</i> you <i>be</i> in the city, and cursed <i>shall</i> you <i>be</i> in the country.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5629O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5629O\"></sup>Cursed <i>shall be</i> your basket and your kneading bowl.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5630P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5630P\"></sup>Cursed <i>shall be</i> the offspring of your body and the produce of your ground, the increase of your herd and the young of your flock.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5631Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5631Q\"></sup>Cursed <i>shall</i> you <i>be</i> when you come in, and cursed <i>shall</i> you <i>be</i> when you go out.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5632R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5632R\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will send upon you curses, confusion, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5632S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5632S\"></sup>rebuke, in all you undertake to do, until you are destroyed and until <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5632T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5632T\"></sup>you perish quickly, on account of the evil of your deeds, because you have forsaken Me.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5633U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5633U\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will make the pestilence cling to you until He has consumed you from the land where you are entering to possess it.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5634V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5634V\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will smite you with consumption and with fever and with inflammation and with fiery heat and with the sword and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5634W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5634W\"></sup>with blight and with mildew, and they will pursue you until <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5634X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5634X\"></sup>you perish.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The heaven which is over your head shall be bronze, and the earth which is under you, iron.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5636Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5636Y\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will make the rain of your land powder and dust; from heaven it shall come down on you until you are destroyed.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5637Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5637Z\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall cause you to be defeated before your enemies; you will go out one way against them, but you will flee seven ways before them, and you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5637AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5637AA\"></sup>be <i>an example of</i> terror to all the kingdoms of the earth.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5638AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5638AB\"></sup>Your carcasses will be food to all birds of the sky and to the beasts of the earth, and there will be no one to frighten <i>them</i> away.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5639AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5639AC\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will smite you with the boils of Egypt and with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5639AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5639AD\"></sup>tumors and with the scab and with the itch, from which you cannot be healed.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will smite you with madness and with blindness and with bewilderment of heart;",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5641AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5641AE\"></sup>grope at noon, as the blind man gropes in darkness, and you will not prosper in your ways; but you shall only be oppressed and robbed continually, with none to save you.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5642AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5642AF\"></sup>You shall betroth a wife, but another man will violate her; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5642AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5642AG\"></sup>you shall build a house, but you will not live in it; you shall plant a vineyard, but you will not use its fruit.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Your ox shall be slaughtered before your eyes, but you will not eat of it; your donkey shall be torn away from you, and will not be restored to you; your sheep shall be given to your enemies, and you will have none to save you.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5644AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5644AH\"></sup>Your sons and your daughters shall be given to another people, while your eyes look on and yearn for them continually; but there will be nothing you can do.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5645AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5645AI\"></sup>A people whom you do not know shall eat up the produce of your ground and all your labors, and you will never be anything but oppressed and crushed continually.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>You shall be driven mad by the sight of what you see.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5647AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5647AJ\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will strike you on the knees and legs with sore boils, from which you cannot be healed, from the sole of your foot to the crown of your head.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5648AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5648AK\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will bring you and your king, whom you set over you, to a nation which neither you nor your fathers have known, and there you shall serve other gods, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5648AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5648AL\"></sup>wood and stone.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5649AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5649AM\"></sup>You shall become a horror, a proverb, and a taunt among all the people where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> drives you.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5650AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5650AN\"></sup>You shall bring out much seed to the field but you will gather in little, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5650AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5650AO\"></sup>the locust will consume it.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5651AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5651AP\"></sup>You shall plant and cultivate vineyards, but you will neither drink of the wine nor gather <i>the grapes</i>, for the worm will devour them.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5652AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5652AQ\"></sup>You shall have olive trees throughout your territory but you will not anoint yourself with the oil, for your olives will drop off.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5653AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5653AR\"></sup>You shall have sons and daughters but they will not be yours, for they will go into captivity.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5654AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5654AS\"></sup>The cricket shall possess all your trees and the produce of your ground.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5655AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5655AT\"></sup>The alien who is among you shall rise above you higher and higher, but you will go down lower and lower.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5656AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5656AU\"></sup>He shall lend to you, but you will not lend to him; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5656AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5656AV\"></sup>he shall be the head, and you will be the tail.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>“So all these curses shall come on you and pursue you and overtake you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5657AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5657AW\"></sup>until you are destroyed, because you would not obey the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God by keeping His commandments and His statutes which He commanded you.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>They shall become <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5658AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5658AX\"></sup>a sign and a wonder on you and your descendants forever.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5659AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5659AY\"></sup>Because you did not serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God with joy and a glad heart, for the abundance of all things;",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>therefore you shall serve your enemies whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will send against you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5660AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5660AZ\"></sup>in hunger, in thirst, in nakedness, and in the lack of all things; and He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5660BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5660BA\"></sup>will put an iron yoke on your neck until He has destroyed you.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5661BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5661BB\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will bring a nation against you from afar, from the end of the earth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5661BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5661BC\"></sup>as the eagle swoops down, a nation whose language you shall not understand,",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>a nation of fierce countenance who will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5662BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5662BD\"></sup>have no respect for the old, nor show favor to the young.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Moreover, it shall eat the offspring of your herd and the produce of your ground until you are destroyed, who also leaves you no grain, new wine, or oil, nor the increase of your herd or the young of your flock until they have caused you to perish.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5664BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5664BE\"></sup>It shall besiege you in all your towns until your high and fortified walls in which you trusted come down throughout your land, and it shall besiege you in all your towns throughout your land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given you.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5665BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5665BF\"></sup>Then you shall eat the offspring of your own body, the flesh of your sons and of your daughters whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given you, during the siege and the distress by which your enemy will oppress you.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>The man who is refined and very delicate among you shall be hostile toward his brother and toward the wife he cherishes and toward the rest of his children who remain,",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>so that he will not give <i>even</i> one of them any of the flesh of his children which he will eat, since he has nothing <i>else</i> left, during the siege and the distress by which your enemy will oppress you in all your towns.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5668BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5668BG\"></sup>The refined and delicate woman among you, who would not venture to set the sole of her foot on the ground for delicateness and refinement, shall be hostile toward the husband she cherishes and toward her son and daughter,",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>and toward her afterbirth which issues from between her legs and toward her children whom she bears; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5669BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5669BH\"></sup>she will eat them secretly for lack of anything <i>else</i>, during the siege and the distress by which your enemy will oppress you in your towns.",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>“If you are not careful to observe all the words of this law which are written in this book, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5670BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5670BI\"></sup>fear this honored and awesome <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5670BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5670BJ\"></sup>name, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God,",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will bring extraordinary plagues on you and your descendants, even severe and lasting plagues, and miserable and chronic sicknesses.",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5672BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5672BK\"></sup>He will bring back on you all the diseases of Egypt of which you were afraid, and they will cling to you.",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>Also every sickness and every plague which, not written in the book of this law, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will bring on you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5673BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5673BL\"></sup>until you are destroyed.",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>Then you shall be left few in number, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5674BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5674BM\"></sup>whereas you were as numerous as the stars of heaven, because you did not obey the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>It shall come about that as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5675BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5675BN\"></sup>delighted over you to prosper you, and multiply you, so the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5675BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5675BO\"></sup>delight over you to make you perish and destroy you; and you will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5675BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5675BP\"></sup>torn from the land where you are entering to possess it.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>Moreover, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5676BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5676BQ\"></sup>scatter you among all peoples, from one end of the earth to the other end of the earth; and there you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5676BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5676BR\"></sup>serve other gods, wood and stone, which you or your fathers have not known.",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5677BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5677BS\"></sup>Among those nations you shall find no rest, and there will be no resting place for the sole of your foot; but there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5677BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5677BT\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give you a trembling heart, failing of eyes, and despair of soul.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>So your life shall hang in doubt before you; and you will be in dread night and day, and shall have no assurance of your life.",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5679BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5679BU\"></sup>In the morning you shall say, ‘Would that it were evening!’ And at evening you shall say, ‘Would that it were morning!’ because of the dread of your heart which you dread, and for the sight of your eyes which you will see.",
			"68": "<sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will bring you back to Egypt in ships, by the way about which I spoke to you, ‘You will never see it again!’ And there you will offer yourselves for sale to your enemies as male and female slaves, but there will be no buyer.”"
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">29 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5681A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5681A\"></sup>These are the words of the covenant which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses to make with the sons of Israel in the land of Moab, besides the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5681B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5681B\"></sup>covenant which He had made with them at Horeb.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Moses summoned all Israel and said to them, “You have seen all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did before your eyes in the land of Egypt to Pharaoh and all his servants and all his land;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5683C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5683C\"></sup>the great trials which your eyes have seen, those great signs and wonders.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Yet to this day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5684D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5684D\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not given you a heart to know, nor eyes to see, nor ears to hear.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I have led you forty years in the wilderness; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5685E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5685E\"></sup>your clothes have not worn out on you, and your sandal has not worn out on your foot.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5686F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5686F\"></sup>You have not eaten bread, nor have you drunk wine or strong drink, in order that you might know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5687G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5687G\"></sup>When you reached this place, Sihon the king of Heshbon and Og the king of Bashan came out to meet us for battle, but we defeated them;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and we took their land and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5688H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5688H\"></sup>gave it as an inheritance to the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of the Manassites.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5689I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5689I\"></sup>So keep the words of this covenant to do them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5689J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5689J\"></sup>that you may prosper in all that you do.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“You stand today, all of you, before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God: your chiefs, your tribes, your elders and your officers, <i>even</i> all the men of Israel,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>your little ones, your wives, and the alien who is within your camps, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5691K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5691K\"></sup>the one who chops your wood to the one who draws your water,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>that you may enter into the covenant with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and into His oath which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is making with you today,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>in order that He may establish you today as His people and that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5693L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5693L\"></sup>He may be your God, just as He spoke to you and as He swore to your fathers, to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Now not with you alone am I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5694M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5694M\"></sup>making this covenant and this oath,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5695N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5695N\"></sup>but both with those who stand here with us today in the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God and with those who are not with us here today",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>(for you know how we lived in the land of Egypt, and how we came through the midst of the nations through which you passed;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>moreover, you have seen their abominations and their idols <i>of</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5697O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5697O\"></sup>wood, stone, silver, and gold, which <i>they had</i> with them);",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5698P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5698P\"></sup>so that there will not be among you a man or woman, or family or tribe, whose heart turns away today from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, to go and serve the gods of those nations; that there will not be among you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5698Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5698Q\"></sup>a root bearing poisonous fruit and wormwood.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>It shall be when he hears the words of this curse, that he will boast, saying, ‘I have peace though I walk in the stubbornness of my heart in order to destroy the watered <i>land</i> with the dry.’",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall never be willing to forgive him, but rather the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5700R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5700R\"></sup>His jealousy will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5700S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5700S\"></sup>burn against that man, and every curse which is written in this book will rest on him, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5700T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5700T\"></sup>blot out his name from under heaven.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will single him out for adversity from all the tribes of Israel, according to all the curses of the covenant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5701U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5701U\"></sup>which are written in this book of the law.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“Now the generation to come, your sons who rise up after you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5702V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5702V\"></sup>the foreigner who comes from a distant land, when they see the plagues of the land and the diseases with which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has afflicted it, will say,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>‘All its land is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5703W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5703W\"></sup>brimstone and salt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5703X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5703X\"></sup>a burning waste, unsown and unproductive, and no grass grows in it, like the overthrow of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5703Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5703Y\"></sup>Sodom and Gomorrah, Admah and Zeboiim, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> overthrew in His anger and in His wrath.’",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>All the nations will say, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5704Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5704Z\"></sup>Why has the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> done thus to this land? Why this great outburst of anger?’",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then <i>men</i> will say, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5705AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5705AA\"></sup>Because they forsook the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers, which He made with them when He brought them out of the land of Egypt.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They went and served other gods and worshiped them, gods whom they have not known and whom He had not allotted to them.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Therefore, the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> burned against that land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5707AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5707AB\"></sup>to bring upon it every curse which is written in this book;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5708AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5708AC\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> uprooted them from their land in anger and in fury and in great wrath, and cast them into another land, as <i>it is</i> this day.’",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5709AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5709AD\"></sup>The secret things belong to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5709AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5709AE\"></sup>the things revealed belong to us and to our sons forever, that we may observe all the words of this law."
		},
		"30": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">30 </span>“So it shall be when all of these things have come upon you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5710A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5710A\"></sup>the blessing and the curse which I have set before you, and you call <i>them</i> to mind <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5710B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5710B\"></sup>in all nations where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has banished you,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5711C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5711C\"></sup>return to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and obey Him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5711D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5711D\"></sup>with all your heart and soul according to all that I command you today, you and your sons,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5712E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5712E\"></sup>restore you from captivity, and have compassion on you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5712F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5712F\"></sup>will gather you again from all the peoples where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5712G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5712G\"></sup>scattered you.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>If your outcasts are at the ends of the earth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5713H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5713H\"></sup>from there the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will gather you, and from there He will bring you back.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5714I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5714I\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will bring you into the land which your fathers possessed, and you shall possess it; and He will prosper you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5714J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5714J\"></sup>multiply you more than your fathers.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Moreover <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5715K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5715K\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will circumcise your heart and the heart of your descendants, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5715L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5715L\"></sup>to love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God with all your heart and with all your soul, so that you may live.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5716M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5716M\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will inflict all these curses on your enemies and on those who hate you, who persecuted you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And you shall again obey the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and observe all His commandments which I command you today.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5718N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5718N\"></sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will prosper you abundantly in all the work of your hand, in the offspring of your body and in the offspring of your cattle and in the produce of your ground, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5718O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5718O\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will again rejoice over you for good, just as He rejoiced over your fathers;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>if you obey the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God to keep His commandments and His statutes which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5719P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5719P\"></sup>are written in this book of the law, if you turn to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5719Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5719Q\"></sup>with all your heart and soul.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“For this commandment which I command you today is not too difficult for you, nor is it out of reach.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>It is not in heaven, that you should say, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5721R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5721R\"></sup>Who will go up to heaven for us to get it for us and make us hear it, that we may observe it?’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Nor is it beyond the sea, that you should say, ‘Who will cross the sea for us to get it for us and make us hear it, that we may observe it?’",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But the word is very near you, in your mouth and in your heart, that you may observe it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“See, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5724S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5724S\"></sup>I have set before you today life and prosperity, and death and adversity;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>in that I command you today <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5725T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5725T\"></sup>to love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, to walk in His ways and to keep His commandments and His statutes and His judgments, that you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5725U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5725U\"></sup>may live and multiply, and that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God may bless you in the land where you are entering to possess it.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But if your heart turns away and you will not obey, but are drawn away and worship other gods and serve them,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I declare to you today that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5727V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5727V\"></sup>you shall surely perish. You will not prolong <i>your</i> days in the land where you are crossing the Jordan to enter and possess it.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5728W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5728W\"></sup>I call heaven and earth to witness against you today, that I have set before you life and death, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5728X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5728X\"></sup>the blessing and the curse. So choose life in order that you may live, you and your descendants,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5729Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5729Y\"></sup>by loving the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, by obeying His voice, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5729Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5729Z\"></sup>by holding fast to Him; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5729AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5729AA\"></sup>for this is your life and the length of your days, that you may live in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5729AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5729AB\"></sup>the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore to your fathers, to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, to give them.”"
		},
		"31": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">31 </span>So Moses went and spoke these words to all Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he said to them, “I am <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5731A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5731A\"></sup>a hundred and twenty years old today; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5731B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5731B\"></sup>I am no longer able to come and go, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has said to me, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5731C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5731C\"></sup>You shall not cross this Jordan.’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5732D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5732D\"></sup>It is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God who will cross ahead of you; He will destroy these nations before you, and you shall dispossess them. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5732E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5732E\"></sup>Joshua is the one who will cross ahead of you, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will do to them just as He did to Sihon and Og, the kings of the Amorites, and to their land, when He destroyed them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5734F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5734F\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will deliver them up before you, and you shall do to them according to all the commandments which I have commanded you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5735G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5735G\"></sup>Be strong and courageous, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5735H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5735H\"></sup>do not be afraid or tremble at them, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5735I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5735I\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is the one who goes with you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5735J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5735J\"></sup>He will not fail you or forsake you.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Moses called to Joshua and said to him in the sight of all Israel, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5736K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5736K\"></sup>Be strong and courageous, for you shall go with this people into the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sworn to their fathers to give them, and you shall give it to them as an inheritance.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5737L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5737L\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is the one who goes ahead of you; He will be with you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5737M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5737M\"></sup>He will not fail you or forsake you. Do not fear or be dismayed.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Moses wrote this law and gave it to the priests, the sons of Levi <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5738N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5738N\"></sup>who carried the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and to all the elders of Israel.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Moses commanded them, saying, “At the end of <i>every</i> seven years, at the time of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5739O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5739O\"></sup>the year of remission of debts, at the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5739P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5739P\"></sup>Feast of Booths,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>when all Israel comes <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5740Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5740Q\"></sup>to appear before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5740R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5740R\"></sup>the place which He will choose, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5740S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5740S\"></sup>you shall read this law in front of all Israel in their hearing.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Assemble the people, the men and the women and children and the alien who is in your town, so that they may hear and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5741T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5741T\"></sup>learn and fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and be careful to observe all the words of this law.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Their children, who have not known, will hear and learn to fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, as long as you live on the land which you are about to cross the Jordan to possess.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5743U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5743U\"></sup>the time for you to die is near; call Joshua, and present yourselves at the tent of meeting, that I may commission him.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5743V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5743V\"></sup>So Moses and Joshua went and presented themselves at the tent of meeting.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5744W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5744W\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared in the tent in a pillar of cloud, and the pillar of cloud stood at the doorway of the tent.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5745X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5745X\"></sup>you are about to lie down with your fathers; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5745Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5745Y\"></sup>this people will arise and play the harlot with the strange gods of the land, into the midst of which they are going, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5745Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5745Z\"></sup>will forsake Me and break My covenant which I have made with them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5746AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5746AA\"></sup>Then My anger will be kindled against them in that day, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5746AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5746AB\"></sup>I will forsake them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5746AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5746AC\"></sup>hide My face from them, and they will be consumed, and many evils and troubles will come upon them; so that they will say in that day, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5746AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5746AD\"></sup>Is it not because our God is not among us that these evils have come upon us?’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But I will surely hide My face in that day because of all the evil which they will do, for they will turn to other gods.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Now therefore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5748AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5748AE\"></sup>write this song for yourselves, and teach it to the sons of Israel; put it on their lips, so that this song may be a witness for Me against the sons of Israel.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5749AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5749AF\"></sup>For when I bring them into the land flowing with milk and honey, which I swore to their fathers, and they have eaten and are satisfied and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5749AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5749AG\"></sup>become prosperous, then they will turn to other gods and serve them, and spurn Me and break My covenant.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then it shall come about, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5750AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5750AH\"></sup>when many evils and troubles have come upon them, that this song will testify before them as a witness (for it shall not be forgotten from the lips of their descendants); for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5750AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5750AI\"></sup>I know their intent which they are developing today, before I have brought them into the land which I swore.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5751AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5751AJ\"></sup>So Moses wrote this song the same day, and taught it to the sons of Israel.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5752AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5752AK\"></sup>Then He commissioned Joshua the son of Nun, and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5752AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5752AL\"></sup>Be strong and courageous, for you shall bring the sons of Israel into the land which I swore to them, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5752AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5752AM\"></sup>I will be with you.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>It came about, when Moses finished writing the words of this law in a book until they were complete,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>that Moses commanded the Levites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5754AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5754AN\"></sup>who carried the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“Take this book of the law and place it beside the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, that it may remain there as a witness against you.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>For I know <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5756AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5756AO\"></sup>your rebellion and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5756AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5756AP\"></sup>your stubbornness; behold, while I am still alive with you today, you have been rebellious against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; how much more, then, after my death?",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Assemble to me all the elders of your tribes and your officers, that I may speak these words in their hearing and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5757AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5757AQ\"></sup>call the heavens and the earth to witness against them.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>For I know that after my death you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5758AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5758AR\"></sup>act corruptly and turn from the way which I have commanded you; and evil will befall you in the latter days, for you will do that which is evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, provoking Him to anger with the work of your hands.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Moses spoke in the hearing of all the assembly of Israel the words of this song, until they were complete:"
		},
		"32": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">32 </span>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5760A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5760A\"></sup>Give ear, O heavens, and let me speak;And let the earth hear the words of my mouth.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5761B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5761B\"></sup>Let my teaching drop as the rain,My speech distill as the dew,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5761C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5761C\"></sup>As the droplets on the fresh grassAnd as the showers on the herb.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5762D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5762D\"></sup>For I proclaim the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5762E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5762E\"></sup>Ascribe greatness to our God!",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5763F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5763F\"></sup>The Rock! His work is perfect,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5763G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5763G\"></sup>For all His ways are just;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5763H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5763H\"></sup>A God of faithfulness and without injustice,Righteous and upright is He.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5764I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5764I\"></sup>They have acted corruptly toward Him,<i>They are</i> not His children, because of their defect;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5764J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5764J\"></sup><i>But are</i> a perverse and crooked generation.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Do you thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5765K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5765K\"></sup>repay the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5765L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5765L\"></sup>O foolish and unwise people?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5765M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5765M\"></sup>Is not He your Father who has bought you?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5765N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5765N\"></sup>He has made you and established you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Remember the days of old,Consider the years of all generations.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5766O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5766O\"></sup>Ask your father, and he will inform you,Your elders, and they will tell you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5767P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5767P\"></sup>When the Most High gave the nations their inheritance,When He separated the sons of man,He set the boundaries of the peoples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5767Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5767Q\"></sup>According to the number of the sons of Israel.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5768R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5768R\"></sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> portion is His people;Jacob is the allotment of His inheritance.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5769S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5769S\"></sup>He found him in a desert land,And in the howling waste of a wilderness;He encircled him, He cared for him,He guarded him as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5769T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5769T\"></sup>the pupil of His eye.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5770U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5770U\"></sup>Like an eagle that stirs up its nest,That hovers over its young,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5770V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5770V\"></sup>He spread His wings and caught them,He carried them on His pinions.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5771W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5771W\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> alone guided him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5771X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5771X\"></sup>And there was no foreign god with him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5772Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5772Y\"></sup>He made him ride on the high places of the earth,And he ate the produce of the field;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5772Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5772Z\"></sup>And He made him suck honey from the rock,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5772AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5772AA\"></sup>oil from the flinty rock,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Curds of cows, and milk of the flock,With fat of lambs,And rams, the breed of Bashan, and goats,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5773AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5773AB\"></sup>With the finest of the wheat—And of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5773AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5773AC\"></sup>blood of grapes you drank wine.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5774AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5774AD\"></sup>But Jeshurun grew fat and kicked—You are grown fat, thick, and sleek—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5774AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5774AE\"></sup>Then he forsook God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5774AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5774AF\"></sup>who made him,And scorned <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5774AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5774AG\"></sup>the Rock of his salvation.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5775AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5775AH\"></sup>They made Him jealous with strange <i>gods</i>;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5775AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5775AI\"></sup>With abominations they provoked Him to anger.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5776AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5776AJ\"></sup>They sacrificed to demons who were not God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5776AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5776AK\"></sup>To gods whom they have not known,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5776AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5776AL\"></sup>New <i>gods</i> who came lately,Whom your fathers did not dread.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“You neglected <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5777AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5777AM\"></sup>the Rock who begot you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5777AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5777AN\"></sup>And forgot the God who gave you birth.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5778AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5778AO\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saw <i>this</i>, and spurned <i>them</i><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5778AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5778AP\"></sup>Because of the provocation of His sons and daughters.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“Then He said, ‘I will hide My face from them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5779AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5779AQ\"></sup>I will see what their end <i>shall be</i>;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5779AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5779AR\"></sup>For they are a perverse generation,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5779AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5779AS\"></sup>Sons in whom is no faithfulness.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5780AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5780AT\"></sup>They have made Me jealous with <i>what</i> is not God;They have provoked Me to anger with their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5780AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5780AU\"></sup>idols.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5780AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5780AV\"></sup>So I will make them jealous with <i>those who</i> are not a people;I will provoke them to anger with a foolish nation,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5781AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5781AW\"></sup>For a fire is kindled in My anger,And burns to the lowest part of Sheol,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5781AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5781AX\"></sup>And consumes the earth with its yield,And sets on fire the foundations of the mountains.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5782AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5782AY\"></sup>I will heap misfortunes on them;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5782AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5782AZ\"></sup>I will use My arrows on them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5783BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5783BA\"></sup><i>They will be</i> wasted by famine, and consumed by plague<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5783BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5783BB\"></sup>And bitter destruction;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5783BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5783BC\"></sup>And the teeth of beasts I will send upon them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5783BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5783BD\"></sup>With the venom of crawling things of the dust.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5784BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5784BE\"></sup>Outside the sword will bereave,And inside terror—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5784BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5784BF\"></sup>Both young man and virgin,The nursling with the man of gray hair.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>‘I would have said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5785BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5785BG\"></sup>I will cut them to pieces,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5785BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5785BH\"></sup>I will remove the memory of them from men,”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Had I not feared the provocation by the enemy,That their adversaries would misjudge,That they would say, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5786BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5786BI\"></sup>Our hand is triumphant,And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not done all this.”’",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5787BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5787BJ\"></sup>For they are a nation lacking in counsel,And there is no understanding in them.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5788BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5788BK\"></sup>Would that they were wise, that they understood this,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5788BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5788BL\"></sup>That they would discern their future!",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5789BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5789BM\"></sup>How could one chase a thousand,And two put ten thousand to flight,Unless their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5789BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5789BN\"></sup>Rock had sold them,And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given them up?",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“Indeed their rock is not like our Rock,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5790BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5790BO\"></sup>Even our enemies themselves judge this.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“For their vine is from the vine of Sodom,And from the fields of Gomorrah;Their grapes are grapes of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5791BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5791BP\"></sup>poison,Their clusters, bitter.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“Their wine is the venom of serpents,And the deadly poison of cobras.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5793BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5793BQ\"></sup>Is it not laid up in store with Me,Sealed up in My treasuries?",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5794BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5794BR\"></sup>Vengeance is Mine, and retribution,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5794BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5794BS\"></sup>In due time their foot will slip;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5794BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5794BT\"></sup>For the day of their calamity is near,And the impending things are hastening upon them.’",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5795BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5795BU\"></sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will vindicate His people,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5795BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5795BV\"></sup>And will have compassion on His servants,When He sees that <i>their</i> strength is gone,And there is none <i>remaining</i>, bond or free.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>“And He will say, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5796BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5796BW\"></sup>Where are their gods,The rock in which they sought refuge?",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5797BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5797BX\"></sup>Who ate the fat of their sacrifices,<i>And</i> drank the wine of their drink offering?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5797BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5797BY\"></sup>Let them rise up and help you,Let them be your hiding place!",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5798BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5798BZ\"></sup>See now that I, I am He,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5798CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5798CA\"></sup>And there is no god besides Me;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5798CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5798CB\"></sup>It is I who put to death and give life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5798CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5798CC\"></sup>I have wounded and it is I who heal,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5798CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5798CD\"></sup>And there is no one who can deliver from My hand.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>‘Indeed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5799CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5799CE\"></sup>I lift up My hand to heaven,And say, as I live forever,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5800CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5800CF\"></sup>If I sharpen My flashing sword,And My hand takes hold on justice,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5800CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5800CG\"></sup>I will render vengeance on My adversaries,And I will repay those who hate Me.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5801CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5801CH\"></sup>I will make My arrows drunk with blood,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5801CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5801CI\"></sup>And My sword will devour flesh,With the blood of the slain and the captives,From the long-haired leaders of the enemy.’",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5802CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5802CJ\"></sup>Rejoice, O nations, <i>with</i> His people;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5802CK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CK&quot;&gt;CK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5802CK\"></sup>For He will avenge the blood of His servants,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5802CL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CL&quot;&gt;CL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5802CL\"></sup>And will render vengeance on His adversaries,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5802CM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CM&quot;&gt;CM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5802CM\"></sup>And will atone for His land <i>and</i> His people.”",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Then Moses came and spoke all the words of this song in the hearing of the people, he, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5803CN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CN&quot;&gt;CN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5803CN\"></sup>Joshua the son of Nun.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>When Moses had finished speaking all these words to all Israel,",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>he said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5805CO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CO&quot;&gt;CO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5805CO\"></sup>Take to your heart all the words with which I am warning you today, which you shall command <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5805CP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CP&quot;&gt;CP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5805CP\"></sup>your sons to observe carefully, <i>even</i> all the words of this law.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>For it is not an idle word for you; indeed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5806CQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CQ&quot;&gt;CQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5806CQ\"></sup>it is your life. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5806CR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CR&quot;&gt;CR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5806CR\"></sup>by this word you will prolong your days in the land, which you are about to cross the Jordan to possess.”",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5807CS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CS&quot;&gt;CS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5807CS\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses that very same day, saying,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5808CT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CT&quot;&gt;CT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5808CT\"></sup>Go up to this mountain of the Abarim, Mount Nebo, which is in the land of Moab opposite Jericho, and look at the land of Canaan, which I am giving to the sons of Israel for a possession.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Then die on the mountain where you ascend, and be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5809CU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CU&quot;&gt;CU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5809CU\"></sup>gathered to your people, as Aaron your brother died on Mount Hor and was gathered to his people,",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5810CV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CV&quot;&gt;CV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5810CV\"></sup>because you broke faith with Me in the midst of the sons of Israel at the waters of Meribah-kadesh, in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5810CW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CW&quot;&gt;CW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5810CW\"></sup>wilderness of Zin, because you did not treat Me as holy in the midst of the sons of Israel.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5811CX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CX&quot;&gt;CX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5811CX\"></sup>For you shall see the land at a distance, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5811CY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CY&quot;&gt;CY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5811CY\"></sup>you shall not go there, into the land which I am giving the sons of Israel.”"
		},
		"33": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">33 </span>Now this is the blessing with which Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5812A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5812A\"></sup>the man of God blessed the sons of Israel before his death.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He said,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5813B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5813B\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came from Sinai,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5813C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5813C\"></sup>And dawned on them from Seir;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5813D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5813D\"></sup>He shone forth from Mount Paran,And He came from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5813E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5813E\"></sup>the midst of ten thousand holy ones;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5813F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5813F\"></sup>At His right hand there was flashing lightning for them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5814G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5814G\"></sup>Indeed, He loves the people;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5814H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5814H\"></sup>All Your holy ones are in Your hand,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5814I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5814I\"></sup>And they followed in Your steps;<i>Everyone</i> receives of Your words.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5815J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5815J\"></sup>Moses charged us with a law,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5815K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5815K\"></sup>A possession for the assembly of Jacob.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5816L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5816L\"></sup>And He was king in Jeshurun,When the heads of the people were gathered,The tribes of Israel together.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5817M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5817M\"></sup>May Reuben live and not die,Nor his men be few.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5818N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5818N\"></sup>And this regarding Judah; so he said,“Hear, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the voice of Judah,And bring him to his people.With his hands he contended for them,And may You be a help against his adversaries.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Of Levi he said,“<i>Let</i> Your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5819O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5819O\"></sup>Thummim and Your Urim <i>belong</i> to Your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5819P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5819P\"></sup>godly man,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5819Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5819Q\"></sup>Whom You proved at Massah,With whom You contended at the waters of Meribah;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5820R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5820R\"></sup>Who said of his father and his mother,‘I did not consider them’;And he did not acknowledge his brothers,Nor did he regard his own sons,For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5820S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5820S\"></sup>they observed Your word,And kept Your covenant.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5821T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5821T\"></sup>They shall teach Your ordinances to Jacob,And Your law to Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5821U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5821U\"></sup>They shall put incense before You,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5821V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5821V\"></sup>whole burnt offerings on Your altar.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, bless his substance,And accept the work of his hands;Shatter the loins of those who rise up against him,And those who hate him, so that they will not rise <i>again</i>.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Of Benjamin he said,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5823W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5823W\"></sup>May the beloved of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> dwell in security by Him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5823X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5823X\"></sup>Who shields him all the day,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5823Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5823Y\"></sup>And he dwells between His shoulders.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Of Joseph he said,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5824Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5824Z\"></sup>Blessed of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <i>be</i> his land,With the choice things of heaven, with the dew,And from the deep lying beneath,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And with the choice yield of the sun,And with the choice produce of the months.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“And with the best things of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5826AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5826AA\"></sup>the ancient mountains,And with the choice things of the everlasting hills,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And with the choice things of the earth and its fullness,And the favor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5827AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5827AB\"></sup>of Him who dwelt in the bush.Let it come to the head of Joseph,And to the crown of the head of the one distinguished among his brothers.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“As the firstborn of his ox, majesty is his,And his horns are the horns of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5828AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5828AC\"></sup>the wild ox;With them he will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5828AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5828AD\"></sup>push the peoples,All at once, <i>to</i> the ends of the earth.And those are the ten thousands of Ephraim,And those are the thousands of Manasseh.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5829AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5829AE\"></sup>Of Zebulun he said,“Rejoice, Zebulun, in your going forth,And, Issachar, in your tents.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5830AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5830AF\"></sup>They will call peoples <i>to</i> the mountain;There they will offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5830AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5830AG\"></sup>righteous sacrifices;For they will draw out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5830AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5830AH\"></sup>the abundance of the seas,And the hidden treasures of the sand.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5831AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5831AI\"></sup>Of Gad he said,“Blessed is the one who enlarges Gad;He lies down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5831AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5831AJ\"></sup>as a lion,And tears the arm, also the crown of the head.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5832AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5832AK\"></sup>Then he provided the first <i>part</i> for himself,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5832AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5832AL\"></sup>For there the ruler’s portion was reserved;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5832AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5832AM\"></sup>And he came <i>with</i> the leaders of the people;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5832AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5832AN\"></sup>He executed the justice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,And His ordinances with Israel.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5833AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5833AO\"></sup>Of Dan he said,“Dan is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5833AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5833AP\"></sup>a lion’s whelp,That leaps forth from Bashan.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Of Naphtali he said,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5834AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5834AQ\"></sup>O Naphtali, satisfied with favor,And full of the blessing of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,Take possession of the sea and the south.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5835AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5835AR\"></sup>Of Asher he said,“More blessed than sons is Asher;May he be favored by his brothers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5835AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5835AS\"></sup>And may he dip his foot in oil.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5836AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5836AT\"></sup>Your locks will be iron and bronze,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5836AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5836AU\"></sup>And according to your days, so will your leisurely walk be.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5837AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5837AV\"></sup>There is none like the God of Jeshurun,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5837AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5837AW\"></sup>Who rides the heavens to your help,And through the skies in His majesty.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5838AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5838AX\"></sup>The eternal God is a dwelling place,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5838AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5838AY\"></sup>And underneath are the everlasting arms;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5838AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5838AZ\"></sup>And He drove out the enemy from before you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5838BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5838BA\"></sup>And said, ‘Destroy!’",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5839BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5839BB\"></sup>So Israel dwells in security,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5839BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5839BC\"></sup>The fountain of Jacob secluded,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5839BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5839BD\"></sup>In a land of grain and new wine;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5839BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5839BE\"></sup>His heavens also drop down dew.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5840BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5840BF\"></sup>Blessed are you, O Israel;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5840BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5840BG\"></sup>Who is like you, a people saved by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5840BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5840BH\"></sup>Who is the shield of your help<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5840BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5840BI\"></sup>And the sword of your majesty!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5840BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5840BJ\"></sup>So your enemies will cringe before you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5840BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5840BK\"></sup>And you will tread upon their high places.”"
		},
		"34": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">34 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5841A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5841A\"></sup>Now Moses went up from the plains of Moab to Mount Nebo, to the top of Pisgah, which is opposite Jericho. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5841B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5841B\"></sup>showed him all the land, Gilead as far as Dan,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and all Naphtali and the land of Ephraim and Manasseh, and all the land of Judah as far as the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5842C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5842C\"></sup>western sea,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and the Negev and the plain in the valley of Jericho, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5843D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5843D\"></sup>the city of palm trees, as far as Zoar.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “This is the land which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5844E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5844E\"></sup>I swore to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, saying, ‘I will give it to your descendants’; I have let you see <i>it</i> with your eyes, but you shall not go over there.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5845F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5845F\"></sup>the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5845G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5845G\"></sup>died there in the land of Moab, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And He buried him in the valley in the land of Moab, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5846H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5846H\"></sup>opposite Beth-peor; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5846I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5846I\"></sup>no man knows his burial place to this day.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Although Moses was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5847J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5847J\"></sup>one hundred and twenty years old when he died, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5847K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5847K\"></sup>his eye was not dim, nor his vigor abated.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So the sons of Israel wept for Moses in the plains of Moab thirty days; then the days of weeping <i>and</i> mourning for Moses came to an end.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now Joshua the son of Nun was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5849L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5849L\"></sup>filled with the spirit of wisdom, for Moses had laid his hands on him; and the sons of Israel listened to him and did as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Since that time <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5850M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5850M\"></sup>no prophet has risen in Israel like Moses, whom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5850N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5850N\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> knew face to face,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>for all the signs and wonders which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent him to perform in the land of Egypt against Pharaoh, all his servants, and all his land,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and for all the mighty power and for all the great terror which Moses performed in the sight of all Israel."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;